title: oakhill potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into shallow sprayed baking dish.
Add chopped eggs.
Cook bacon and onion in first measure of butter in large pot until onion is transparent.
Stir in flour, mustard and salt.
Add 1 cup of milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add remaining milk and boil again.
Stir in grated cheese.
(If too thick to pour easily, add more milk.)
Pour over potatoes, covering the entire surface.
Top with buttered bread crumbs made by melting second measure of butter and stirring in the crumbs.
Refrigerate until needed.
Bake, uncovered, at 180°C for 30 to 45 minutes, until heated through and lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs and vinegar together. Mix flour and butter until crumbly in large bowl. Add egg mixture and mix well.

title: hot browns
directions: Melt butter and add enough flour to make a reasonable thick roux (enough to absorb all of the butter).
Add milk and parmesan cheese.
Add egg to thicken sauce; but do not allow to boil. Remove from heat.
Fold in whipped cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
For each Hot Brown, place 2 slices of toast on a metal or flame proof dish.
Cover toast with liberal amount of turkey. Pour a generous amount of sauce over turkey and toast.
Sprinkle with additional parmesan cheese.
Place entire dish under a broiler until the sauce is speckled brown and bubbles.
Remove from broiler, cross 2 pieces of bacon on top and serve immediately.

title: kidney bean salad(for my brother, steve, with love)
directions: Drain beans; rinse and drain again.
Add together all ingredients with mayonnaise or dressing to your taste.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add cream cheese and beat until fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Turn mixer to low speed and fold in flour.

title: apple dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread apples, then add crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit, then a layer of coconut, then a layer of nuts.
Pour melted butter over top of mixture. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
May be served plain or with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with Fritos scoops or tortilla chips.

title: apricot pineapple jam
directions: Rinse apricots; simmer, covered, in 2 1/2 cups of water until tender.
Mash apricots.
Add pineapple, lemon and sugar.
Simmer, stirring frequently, until thick and clear, about 45 minutes. Ladle into hot scalded jars.
Seal.
Makes about six 1/2-pint jars.

title: italiano steak
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 pieces, serving size.
Coat with salt, oregano and pepper.
In slow cooker or crock-pot, pour spaghetti sauce over meat. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until meat is tender. Turn control to high.
Add onions (may use fresh onions). Cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Italian green beans and toasted garlic cheese bread.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: granola by glenda
directions: Heat oil, honey, flavoring and pour over all other ingredients. Pour into a large cookie sheet.
Heat in oven for 45 minutes at 300°.
Stir occasionally.

title: fruit pie topping
directions: Soften butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Topping will be lumpy. Spread over pie and bake as directed.
Makes enough topping for one pie.

title: greek sauerkraut
directions: Mix all ingredients except caraway seeds and sausage. Top with caraway seeds and sausage. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: grandma's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add milk gradually. Beat 2 eggs separately and add to this mixture. Cook until desired thickness on medium-high heat. Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine. Stir until well blended. Serve hot.

title: noodle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian party punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine Hawaiian punch, grapefruit juice and grenadine.
Add strawberries.
Just before serving, add lemon-lime soda and ice.
Float orange slices on top.
Makes 32 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: Simmer chicken in water, salt, pepper, celery and onion for 1 hour.
Remove chicken, cool and strain broth.
In large pan, combine broth, condensed chicken broth, cream of chicken soup, chopped onion, carrots, vermouth or water, garlic, basil and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Add cubed chicken and tortellini. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add broccoli.
Simmer an additional 20 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: o-oey goey butter cake
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 egg, butter and cake mix with a fork.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fried turkey breast
directions: Cut turkey into strips and remove skin.
Soak turkey strips in buttermilk at least one hour.
Drain well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge in flour and deep-fry.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a small mixer bowl, cream the margarine; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool about 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts; cook until brown.
Add soda; mix well.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool; break apart.

title: harvest chutney
directions: In large pan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, ginger, mustard seed, peppercorns and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boil.
Mix in tomatoes, apples, onions and zucchini.
Boil until almost thickened, about 4 hours.
Add raisins and candied ginger.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: amaretto ball
directions: Chop fruit fine in blender or processor.
Add cream cheese and Amaretto and blend.
Shape into a ball and put in a glass dish and cover.
Chill and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: chip beef ball
directions: Leave 1 package of dried beef to roll your ball in.
Get cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine remaining ingredients to cream cheese and form into a ball.
Roll your ball in dried beef. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: grandma's welsh cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening (as for pie crust).
Add raisins, then add eggs and milk; mix.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with round cutter and bake either on lightly greased skillet (griddle) or baking sheet in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Most Welsh prefer to bake in skillet - electric can be used.)
Grill over medium-low heat in electric skillet.
Bake on one side about 4 or 4 1/2 minutes.
Turn and bake on other side.
Dough can be refrigerated (in a roll) for a couple of weeks.
Slice off regular number and bake as required.

title: hot beef sandwich
directions: Brown ground beef, celery, onions and green pepper in skillet; drain.
Return to skillet.
Add tomato juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Grind dry bread and add to mixture in skillet.
Mix well.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour.
Serve on hot rolls.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 2 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Add to oatmeal mix.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda together and add to mixture.
Bake in oblong pan 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: aunt hellen's white fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and salt into pan.
Cool over medium heat until soft balls form in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat mixture over medium speed until fudge starts to harden.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: black magic cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an oblong pan or 30 to 35 minutes for a layer cake.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Mix and leave, covered, overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, bake cake mix according to directions in two layers.
Split each layer to make 4 layers in all.
Put coconut mixture between layers and on top of cake.
Seal in covered cake container and refrigerate up to 4 days before serving. Cake absorbs the icing.

title: golden turkey quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cook celery in butter until tender.
Stir in turkey and pimento.
Beat together eggs, milk, mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Stir egg mixture into turkey mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until knife inserted near center, comes out clean.
Good way to use leftover turkey or chicken.

title: fried dandelions
directions: Pick 20 fully bloomed dandelions, soak them for about 20 minutes in warm water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Water should just cover blooms.
Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Dip the dandelions in mixture, then roll in flour or crumbs.
Fry at medium heat until crisp and golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: sunshine slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and carrots together.
Cover and chill.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over cabbage and carrots.
Mix well.
Chill well in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings, about 75 calories per serving.

title: crab spread mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup, then combine gelatin and soup mixture.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and soup mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 to 10 minutes until tender; drain.
Place in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix together mayonnaise, egg, onion, soup and cheese.
Pour this on top of broccoli.
Melt butter and stir in stuffing.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: frittata
directions: Preheat broiler.
Heat butter and oil together in 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Saute the mushrooms and shallots over medium-low heat, until soft and lightly golden, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Melt butter; mix with cracker crumbs.
Place 1/2 in a large pan.
Beat together milk, Dream Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Spread 1/2 mixture on cracker crumbs in pan.
Add strawberries and remaining cream mixture and top with remaining cracker crumbs. Chill for 24 hours.

title: almond crescent cookies
directions: Measure 1 2/3 cups almonds.
Whirl in blender or grind fine. Finely chop remaining almonds and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and ground almonds.
With fingers, work in butter and vanilla extract, until mixture cleans bowl.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together the peanuts, corn syrup, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2 qt. glass dish.
Microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Stir well with wooden spoon (plastic or rubber will melt).
Microwave on high for 4 more minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Microwave on high for 2 minutes or until golden.	Stir in baking soda until bubbling begins to subside.	Pour onto greased cookie sheet, stretching with two forks while candy is still hot.
When cool, break into pieces and enjoy.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place chicken and vegetables in baking dish.
Stir together soup, chicken broth and pepper; pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and butter; stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: english muffins
directions: Add butter, salt and sugar to milk.
Cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in water.
Add yeast, egg and 2 cups flour to cooled milk.
Stir to blend well, then knead in remaining flour until firm and elastic.
Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Roll into 4-inch circles.
Leave on board.
Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
When light, sprinkle with corn meal, if desired.
Bake slowly on hot ungreased heavy griddle or frying pan for 7 minutes on each side.
Brown slowly.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Mix together brown sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Put in the bottom of an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Cut up 4 to 5 peaches into fourths if peaches are small or eighths if peaches are large. Place these pieces on the mixture so that the pits are upward.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 400° until top is brown.
Serve hot or cold. Store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can onions.
Pour into casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes uncovered.

title: easy skillet stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat. Pour off fat.
Blend in mushroom soup and sour cream; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Stir often.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onions together until tender.
In the meantime, melt the margarine and stir the flour, salt, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce and chicken base together.
Add chicken broth.
When mixed thoroughly, add the hot milk and cheese to melt.
Last of all, add the broccoli and onions.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Mix bananas and pineapple together first and the bananas won't turn brown.

title: homemade beef barbecue
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and	simmer	in crock-pot on medium heat for about 2 1/2 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: bacalaitos fritos(codfish fritters)
directions: Achiote:
Achiote is annatto seeds cooked in vegetable oil.
In small skillet, heat 1/2 cup olive oil or vegetable oil.
When oil is very hot, add 1 tablespoon annatto seeds.
They can be obtained at most supermarkets in 8 ounce jars.
Turn heat to low and cook the seed, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
During cooking, the oil will turn a bright orange red color.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Using a small strainer, pour into a glass jar.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool, then frost.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together until light yellow.
Add sugar and beat.
Add dry ingredients and beat good.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and apples.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: cornmeal pastry
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and salt; cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle cold water (1 tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface; stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into 48 balls.
Place in greased 1 3/4-inch tart pan, shaping each ball into a shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks. Yield: 4 dozen pastry cups.
Serve filled with chili.

title: orange yams
directions: Heat yams with sugar, orange slices and juice.
This may also be used to glaze ham or chicken.

title: gold rush griddie cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening until the mixture is mealy.
Add egg, milk and raisins and mix (dough is stiff).
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2 inch cookie cutter.
Heat griddle and oil lightly.
Place cookies on it.
As the bottoms brown, the tops become puffy.
Turn with spatula and brown other side.

title: fruity cream cheese sandwich filling
directions: Soften cream cheese; add milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in fruit and spread on breads.
For teas or special occasions, alternate layers of wheat and white bread until there are three pieces of bread with filling between.
Chill in refrigerator for about 30 minutes, then cut with decorative cutters.
To keep sandwiches fresh, cover with slightly damp white paper towel, then with plastic wrap.

title: orange-marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in baking dish.
Add pork and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour or overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain pork, reserving marinade.
Place pork on baking sheet and season with pepper. Roast until cooked through, about 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together, fold in pecans and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 40 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: deli-style cole slaw
directions: Prepare cabbage and carrots.
Mix together in a large stock pot.
(It will reduce in size after dressing is added.)
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt together in a small bowl. Toss dressing with cabbage mixture until well coated.
Add pepper to taste.
Let set about 15 minutes until wilted.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook syrup to hard crack stage (305°).
Stir until sugar is fully dissolved.
Add margarine when syrup comes to a boil, stirring frequently after syrup reaches 230°.
Add nuts when mixture reaches 280° and stir constantly thereafter.
Remove from heat and stir in soda, mixing thoroughly.
Pour onto two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheets.
As candy cools, stretch it until thin by lifting edges of candy and pulling it from the edges.
Loosen from cookie sheets and break into pieces when it cools.

title: venison chili & cheddar oven bake
directions: Spray vegetable oil all around inside of large casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown venison, garlic and onion in a frying pan.
Mix well with rest of ingredients and pour into prepared casserole dish.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 25 minutes until contents begin to bubble.
Serve with hot buttered tortillas.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in margarine.
Add water, bouillon, chili powder, cumin and garlic powder.
Cover; simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in sour cream; heat through (do not boil).
Top each tortilla with lettuce, then chicken mixture.
Garnish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot crabby punch
directions: Put all ingredients into a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Do not cover!
After it boils, turn heat down low and let it simmer for 20 minutes.
Turn off heat and remove the spices with slotted spoon.
Pour punch into mugs.
Add a cinnamon stick and drink.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: perfectly luscious pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.
Serves 8.

title: scallops oriental
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spray baking pan with vegetable oil.
Rinse scallops in cold water and drain.
Place in baking pan.
In a saucepan, combine honey, mustard, curry powder and lemon juice. Brush scallops with sauce.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until browned.

title: isabel's lime salad with 7-up
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese until well blended.
Slowly add jello that has been dissolved in hot water and cooled.
Then add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold or a pretty glass bowl. Chill until set.

title: flag day cheese log
directions: Mix both cheeses in a bowl.
Stir in celery and onion.
Chill for 2 hours.
Shape into a log.
Design a flag on top, using walnuts for stars and slices of pimento for stripes.
Serve cold. Goes great with crackers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Mix 3/4 cup mushroom soup into meat.
Pack firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pinto beans with potatoes(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cover the pinto beans with water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until beans are just tender.
Add the potato chunks, celery and salt, along with more water if necessary to cover.
Continue to cook over low heat.
Just before the potatoes and beans are tender, gently fry the onion in oil in a large, heavy skillet or stew pot.
Using a slotted spoon, stir until well blended and heated through.
Serve hot over rice.

title: cherry-o-cream pie
directions: Let cheese soften to room temperature; beat until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk; stir until blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour over pie crust.
Chill 2 or 3 hours before garnishing with cherry pie filling.
(Pour cherries on top of pie.)

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl at one time, mixing well. Stir until mixture is moistened and quickly pour batter into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Spread batter evenly and bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Check doneness with a toothpick.
Put slices of Velveeta cheese on top of the bread and bake for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Spread evenly. Spoon serving onto plate.

title: tuna sandwich melts
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buns, until well blended.
Fill each bun with 1/2 cup tuna mixture.
Place 2 sandwiches on paper towel.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until thoroughly heated. Repeat with remaining sandwiches.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix both boxes of Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix the gelatin with 1/2 cup cold water. Grind oranges, apples and cranberries.
Add to Jell-O mixture. Add other ingredients. Pour into large Pyrex dish and refrigerate until set.
Top with Frosted Topping.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir together to distribute	evenly.
Put in airtight
container.
May
be stored up to 6 to 8 months.
Makes about 22
cups	of Hot Roll Mix.

title: strawberry-banana congealed salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir until jello is dissolved.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas and sour cream. Fold into jello.
Pour into a mold or a dish.
Chill.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; cook until smooth and thick. Cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy and add cooked mixture. Chill.
Serve with thinly sliced apples which have been soaked in lemon juice or sprinkled with Fruit-Fresh.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli or cauliflower soup
directions: Cook fresh broccoli or cauliflower; set aside.
Saute onions in oleo until tender.
Add water and chicken bouillon cubes; boil until dissolved.
Add noodles (optional).
Cook, uncovered, until noodles are tender.
Add garlic salt, milk and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped broccoli or cauliflower.
Serve.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Mix in taco sauce.
Break up approximately 1/2 bag tortilla chips into beef mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake to heat through and melt cheese.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together and bake until brown on top at 350°.

title: phil's garlic bread burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook hamburgers in oblong shape. Place burgers on garlic bread.
Top with cheese and onions (optional).
Cut bread into individual pieces.
Wrap with foil. Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and enjoy a different type of burger!

title: california dessert
directions: Layer cake slices in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with pudding and top all with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the egg and vanilla.
Sift and add flour and baking soda; add chopped nuts, cherries and coconut. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight or several hours.
Best when grilled.
Try over pork chops.

title: apple-cherry crunch(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place chopped apples in medium bowl. Drain cherries, saving juice. Add cherries to apples.
Set aside.

title: none-such prize cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well. Stir in crumbled mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 to 10 minutes before stirring.
Add 2 cups of the flour and all other ingredients.
With electric mixer, blend at low speed, then beat 2 minutes.
Beat in remaining 2 cups flour by hand.
Cover and let rise until doubles (30 to 40 minutes).
Stir batter down to deflate.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and let rise again.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: coconut or chocolate pie
directions: Put milk in pan and add 1/2 of sugar.
Do not stir until milk comes to a boil.
Put in butter.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs in a light paste.
When milk comes to a boil pour your mixture in the milk and stir until it thickens.
Add vanilla and add coconut or cocoa.
If you make chocolate, add your cocoa in with the flour mixture.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Combine everything; add the rice.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Bring tea bags to boil in 2 cups of water.
Add sugar, orange juice and lemonade.
Mix well.
Add 7 cups water and bourbon. Freeze.

title: chicken and potato salad(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Place the potatoes and salt in a soup pot and add enough water to cover the potatoes. Bring to a boil

over high heat and let boil for 5 minutes or until the potatoes are tender; drain, rinse with cold water and drain again. Place the potatoes in a large bowl and add the chicken, asparagus, radishes and dressing; toss well. Serve warm or cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: liver sausage spread
directions: Stir all ingredients, except eggs, until smooth.
Add eggs. Roll into ball and chill in the refrigerator.

title: cheese danish
directions: Unroll one package of rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Pinch together in middle to form a solid bottom.
Cream the cheese, sugar, egg yolk and flavoring together until smooth.
Spread over pastry.

title: rice salad
directions: Bring water and chicken broth to a boil.
Add rice and bay leaves.
Cover and cook on low 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Transfer rice into large bowl and fluff.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Remove all green from rind, peeling about 1/4-inch thick. Remove any pink melon left on rind. Cut rind into 1-inch cubes. Makes about 3 quarts of cubes. Soak overnight in saltwater to cover, using 1/4 cup salt to each quart of water. Drain; rinse rind in cold water. Put rind in a large kettle; cover with cold water and bring to a boil. Simmer until barely tender, about 10 minutes; drain well.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cook until thick and pour over hot cake.

title: sausage cheese snacks
directions: Brown sausage and add Velveeta and melt. Put on party rye and bake in 350° oven until rye is crisp. Approx 15 min.

title: flying saucers(kids dish)
directions: Place 1 piece of bologna on microwave-safe plate with a scoop of mashed potatoes in middle.
Smother with cheese and zap for 45 seconds or until cheese melts.
Serve hot with favorite fruit.

title: date cake with chocolate(from a little league mother)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; mix well and set aside. In a medium bowl, mix melted margarine, 1 1/4 cups of sugar and eggs.
Add salt, 3/4 teaspoon
soda and flour which have been sifted; mix well.
Add date
mixture. Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top of mixture 1/2 cup of sugar, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
A great potluck or picnic cake.
It needs no frosting.

title: angel food cake like mom used to make
directions: Add egg whites to egg mixture and water called for on package.
Beat as directed.
Sift flour and sugar with package flour mixture and fold into eggs and water.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, then reduce heat to 325° for an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: virginia bethea's danish cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream egg and sugar well; add flour and vanilla and blend in. With hands, work in the butter until dough slips in fingers.
Form ball; roll out and cut with any shape cookie cutter.
Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mix.
Bake at 350° until light brown (don't overbake).
(Dough may be formed into ball and chilled a day or 2 before shaping and baking.)

title: rib roast of lamb with herb dijon crust
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub rib roast with cut side of 2 halves of garlic.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Place fat side up in large shallow roasting pan. Roast 30 minutes.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pat mixture into a loaf shape and put in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
About 10 to 15 minutes before serving, baste meat loaf with pan drippings while still in pan.
Pour the tomato sauce and soup over the meat loaf and let cook remaining time.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Arrange chicken tenders on bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, stuffing mix cubes and flavor packet.
Pour cream of chicken and mushroom soup over top, then milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat peanut bread
directions: In
large
bowl stir well flour, peanuts, sugar, baking powder and
salt;	set
aside.
With
whisk or fork beat milk, peanut butter
and
egg
until
well
blended.
Add
to
flour mixture; stir just to moisten.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan in preheated
oven
to 65 minutes or until pick inserted in center
comes
out clean.	Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes. Remove
from
pan; cool completely on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: jiffy cake dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1 cup milk to pudding; blend in cream cheese and second cup of milk.
Pour mixture over cooled cake.
Put drained pineapple over pudding mixture; spread Cool Whip over this.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place meat in a large 4 quart beanpot.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix, add other soups and Gravy Master.
Add vegetables and water.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Don't peek.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple; add to cream cheese along with seasoning salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in container to serve.
May be made a day in advance.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Top with pecans before serving.

title: golden gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 9-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine flours and next 5 ingredients.
In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat margarine, sugar and applesauce until smooth.
Add egg whites and buttermilk; beat well.
Turn mixer to low speed and beat in flour mixture.
(Fold in raisins if using.)
Pour into pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fettucini carbonara
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain well and crumble.
Cook fettucini according to package directions.
Drain well and place in warm serving dish large enough for tossing.
Add crumbled bacon, butter, cream cheese and eggs.
Toss until fettucini is well coated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: box 144 style potatoes
directions: Place the oil in a large nonstick skillet.
Add the potatoes and garlic.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat for 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir, then continue cooking for another 3 or 4 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 3 or 4 minutes. Stir, then cook for 3 or 4 minutes or until golden and tender. Serves 2 to 3.

title: beef casserole chinese style
directions: Cook beef in frying pan until brown and crumbly.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange thawed peas over the meat. Cover with celery.
Mix together the soup, milk, salt, pepper and onion; pour over the peas and meat.
Sprinkle potato chips on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued spoon burgers
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes. Brown 1 1/2 pounds hamburger and add to simmering mixture.
Let simmer at least 20 minutes more.
Remove lemon slices; serve on hamburger buns.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute
onions
in
1/2 of butter.
Add soup, cheese and sour cream.
Blend.
Add this mixture to hash browns.
Mix 1/2 of butter
(melted) with crushed cornflakes and put on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Beat egg yolks; add water and beat in flour until smooth.
Trim ends from pickles and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Dry on paper towels. Dip pickles in egg batter and fry without crowding.
Fry until slightly brown; remove and drain on paper towels.
Serve at once.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In
a large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done. Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: candy o easy
directions: In large pot, put first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil; boil 5 minutes only.
Remove from heat and add chips and vanilla.
Stir until smooth and thick.
Pour into 6 x 12 x 2-inch dish or whatever you have for a good size dish of candy.

title: lite and delicious waffles
directions: Grease and heat a waffle iron.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, soda, oil and sugar.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Add flour and whisk until smooth.
Pour batter into waffle iron and bake until steaming stops and waffles are light brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together first four ingredients until bananas are pulverized.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix in the banana mix and add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes for small loaves or 1 hour for large loaves.
Cool in the pan.

title: chicken fingers
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise and salsa.
Set aside 6 tablespoons.
Add chicken strips to remaining mixture and toss well.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Grill chicken 5-inches from heat, turning once, for 4 minutes or until tender.
Serve with remaining 6 tablespoons of mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 appetizer servings.

title: goulash(rodeo special)
directions: Cook noodles in water; drain and add butter and set aside. Brown ground beef, pepper and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings, blending thoroughly.
Simmer uncovered 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cheese and noodles.
Heat slowly for 10 minutes.

title: good green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix be frozen.
Makes 80 (4 ounce) cups or 2 1/2 gallons.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nutmeg.
Pour in deep pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, then for 1 hour at 325°.

title: kielbasa-cheese potato topping
directions: In blender, combine egg, lemon juice, mustard, and salt. Blend well and with motor running, gradually add oil until mixture is consistency of mayonnaise.
In large heavy saucepan, melt cheese spread.
Add the egg mixture, sausage, ad jalapenos, stirring to blend.
Remove from heat and store in refrigerator in an airtight container. To serve, heat mixture and spoon over baked potatoes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan and cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and warm mixing bowl.
Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add cooked syrup and mix well. Pour into a 6 x 10-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, onions, celery and carrots until tender. Heat the cream cheese, cream of chicken soup and margarine in the microwave. Beat until smooth. Put all ingredients in a crock-pot. Add 2 cups milk and salt and pepper to taste.

title: marshmallow fudge(never fail)
directions: Put first four ingredients in large bowl and set aside.
In large heavy kettle, put the last 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes, then pour on first four ingredients in bowl.
Mix until smooth and put in large long pan that has been greased.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in 2 loaf pans.

title: congealed beet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain beets and set aside. Add beet juice, vinegar, salt and onion to gelatin.
Partly chill, then add beets and cucumbers.
Chill until firm.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet (remove casing from sausage, if necessary).
Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Remove meat and place in ovensafe baking dish.
Stir onion, green pepper and garlic in skillet and saut for 5 minutes.
Add to meat.
Add tomatoes, water, oregano, basil, salt and spaghetti to casserole. Push spaghetti down into liquid.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Cover with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Leave uncovered.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese is melted.
Serve hot, right from the oven!! Makes 4 servings.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and green peppers.
Layer tortilla chips, chicken mixture and cheese.
Mix chili powder, garlic, soups, picante sauce and chicken stock together.
Pour over layers.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
(Will work better with hands.)
Shape into rolls.
Chill and slice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; drain and chop. Put into 9 x 12 baking dish.

title: puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water, margarine and salt to a boil.
Reduce heat; add flour.
Stir over heat until dough leaves the pan at the sides.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Great stuffed with chicken or tuna salad.
Also for dessert pastries.

title: dressing
directions: Crumble breads.
Add onion, celery, sage, margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Add to bread mixture with enough broth to mix.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: the bricks pancakes
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk and refrigerate overnight.
Add slightly beaten eggs and melted butter to mixture.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Add buttermilk mixture, stirring enough to barely moisten dry ingredients.
For each pancake, drop 1/2 cup batter onto lightly greased griddle.
Cook until surface is bubbly and edges are slightly dry, then turn and cook other side.
This recipe makes about 26 pancakes.
Reduce ingredients by half for smaller family.

title: cream cheese peach pie
directions: Mix these ingredients together and then add to it 2 full cups of sliced peaches, sliced about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Have a 10-inch deep dish greased with oleo or butter.

title: cinderella's cake
directions: Mix oats and water; let stand until cool.
Stir together next 4 ingredients.
In large bowl stir margarine, sugars until blended. Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly. Stir in oatmeal.
Turn into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread with quick topping while cake is warm.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.
Top with nuts and/or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chocolate powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix the flour, salt and baking powder and add.
Add together.
Chill several hours.
Roll in balls, then in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle half of pecans in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan. Cut biscuits in half and shake in a bag with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry squares
directions: Chill and cut into squares.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients then add cool whip.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: stuffed italian peppers
directions: Take seeds out of peppers, wash and dry, chop anchovies and olives in small pieces, add to bread crumbs.
Moisten with oil, stuff peppers, seal with piece of bread or stem of pepper.
Bake about 3/4 hour in 350° oven.
Pour a little oil over peppers before baking, add just a little salt.

title: acorn squash-sausage bake
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Place cut side down in a baking pan.
Add 1/2-inch of water.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: kugel souffle
directions: Cook noodles.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and vanilla in order listed.
Fold in noodles and raisins.
Add milk, place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes and 350° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight and reheat the next day.

title: home canned sour cherry pie filling
directions: Combine pitted cherries with 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water. Boil gently without stirring for 5 minutes, or until foaming ceases.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix until cornstarch is well dispersed.
Add to the cooked cherries.
Bring to a gently boil and hold for 1 minute.
Pour while boiling into hot jars.
Place lids and bands on firmly.
Immediately process 30 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Spread rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add water. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up; dilute mushroom soup with milk.
Spread over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with
1 (6 ounce) semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Let stand for 5
minutes. Combine
cup	powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter
and 2 to 4 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Spread chocolate
evenly. Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.
Cool.	Cut into bars.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and applesauce. Beat well. Sift flour with soda, salt and spices. Add alternately with milk, beating thoroughly. Pour into well oiled loaf pan. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook meat; drain off fat.
Measure fat back into pan.
Brown onion in fat.
Add the tomato paste, water, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer all ingredients for one hour; if needed, add more water.
Serve on cooked spaghetti.
One or two teaspoons of grated Parmesan cheese may be used per serving.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 23 g, protein 19 g, fat 17 g, calories 321. One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange, 1 vegetable exchange.

title: shelled manicotti
directions: Cook jumbo shells until tender.
While they're boiling, mix together, in separate bowl, Ricotta cheese, 2 beaten eggs, oregano, 1 package Mozzarella cheese, salt, pepper, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Brown ground beef and drain, then add spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter and sugar in food processor 1/2 batch at a time.
Make into balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate wafers; dip balls into it and refrigerate until set. Makes about 40.

title: asian peanut dipping sauce
directions: Combine carrots, jalapeno, green onion and ginger in food process. Whirl until finely chopped.
Add peanut butter, soy sauce and water.
Process until smooth, scraping down side of bowl as needed.
Add additional water if thinner consistency is desired. Serve immediately or refrigerate, covered for up to 1 day.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add buttermilk and oil.
Stir in flour.
Add soda, sugar and salt.
Add bran flakes.
Stir.
Put into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° until done.
Keep unused batter in refrigerator and use when needed.
A half batch may be made.

title: peach pickle 2
directions: Let sugar, vinegar and cloves come to a good boil.
Drop in the peaches and let them get hot through until they can be pierced through with straw.
Put in jars and cover them with hot vinegar.

title: cereal muffins
directions: Mix sugar, oil and boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well in large bowl with wooden spoon.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Needs to set several hours or overnight before using.
Do not re-stir.

title: "quick" won't last long cake
directions: Add water, eggs and oil as per cake mix package.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
I coat it with sugar; it comes out golden brown.
Bake at 350° until tested done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding mix according to directions on box.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
In rectangular serving dish, place layer of whole vanilla wafers.
Top this with layer of sliced bananas. Pour pudding mixture over bananas.
For topping, add sliced bananas to cover and stack vanilla wafers around edge of dish.

title: hot sauce(salsa)
directions: Cook tomatoes for 30 minutes.
Add other ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
Seal in 3 pint jars.
Additional onion, brown sugar and/or red pepper can be added to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips or use as a base for chili.

title: butterscotch bubble
directions: Cut biscuits in half; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Add melted butter and pudding; mix well.
Add cut biscuits.
Make sure biscuits are well coated, then spread into deep dish baker.
(You may have to use your hands to spread the dough.
The whole pan doesn't need to be covered; the dough will spread.)
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add lemon rind.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Pour into 3 medium loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn from pans to cake rack covered with wax paper.
Drizzle the sugar and juice over the loaves.
Cool.
Double wrap to freeze.
Cream cheese spread on slices is delicious.

title: gourmet beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in next 8 ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cook
and drain noodles.
Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and onion and add to noodles. Pour one cup of meat sauce into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with a layer of noodles.
Sprinkle with a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, juice and cornstarch in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
When thickened, pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Put top crust on and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: lo-fat texas trash
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Toss with cereal.
Place on shallow nonstick baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir halfway through baking.
Cool before serving.
Contains 13% fat.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly in large bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: dilled okra
directions: Put 1/2 teaspoon dill seed in bottom of each quart jar.
Pack washed fresh okra as tightly as possible in each jar, being careful not to bruise.
Add 1 or 2 pods red and green hot pepper and one or more garlic cloves to each jar.
Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Cover okra with mixture.
Seal.
Ready to eat in 4 to 6 weeks.

title: polynesian spareribs
directions: Separate ribs in single pieces; remove all fat.
Place in large baking pan and cover with the pineapple juice and juice from pineapple rings.
Cover with foil and bake in center of slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and empty off 3/4 of juice.
Peel oranges and cut in 1/2-inch rings; slice bananas lengthwise.
Then put layer of ribs and top with orange rings; cover with brown sugar.
Layer ribs, pineapple and sugar.
Then layer ribs, bananas and sugar, ending with ribs topped with sugar. Return to oven and bake on high (450°) at top until the sugar melts and coats ribs with caramel.

title: yankee doodle apple dessert
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in unbeaten egg and vanilla. Fold in apples and nuts.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch pie pan. (Batter will be very stiff.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and crusty.

title: angel food cake with strawberries
directions: Break up the cake and layer 1/2 of it on bottom of bowl.
Put strawberries in blender (1 carton at a time) and blend.
Spread these over cake.
Whip cream and add 1/2 cup sugar per carton. Put whipping cream over strawberries.
Repeat these layers and add a few fresh strawberries to top for garnish.
Serves 8.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish.
Mix broth and soup. Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, margarine and buttermilk.
Pour over chicken. Cook at 350° until brown.

title: peas with mushrooms and onions
directions: Cook peas as indicated on package; drain well.
In saucepan, lightly saute mushrooms and onion in margarine until tender.
Add salt, pepper and allspice.
Serve hot.

title: cottage potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and eggs.
Mix sour cream and Italian dressing.
Add to potato mixture, tossing lightly.
Set aside. Combine cottage cheese, celery, radishes, olives, green onion and salt.
Toss with potato mixture.
Pack into a 5-cup ring mold. Chill.
Unmold and garnish with tomato wedges and parsley.

title: all american clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in frying pan until crisp.
Remove and break into one-inch pieces.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Add clam liquor and potatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are done (about 15 minutes).
Blend in bacon pieces, minced clams and other ingredients.
Heat, but do not boil.
Bacon may be used for garnish.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil, confectioners sugar and cheese.
Heat oil (about 1-inch deep) in a small frying pan.
Pour batter through funnel into hot oil, using swirling pattern.
Turn with a fork when golden brown.
When second side is brown, remove from oil and place on a plate.
Top at once with shredded cheese or confectioners sugar or enjoy plain.
Leftover batter will keep in refrigerator for about a week.
Serves many.

title: black walnut butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter.
Combine flour, cornstarch, and sugar.
Add to butter. Stir in nuts.
Roll into 3/4- inch balls. Place 1 inch apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 - 25 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: cheese tidbits(biscuit type)
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
(Cheese could be warmer.)
Mix by hand. Roll into small balls.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze. Add 1 large bottle of ginger ale before serving.

title: ham stir-fried rice
directions: Cook rice and allow to cool.
Scramble eggs, cook and set aside.
Cook bacon, drain and crumble; set aside.

title: rigatone mamma mia(with ricotta cheese, prosciutto, eggplant and tomato sauce)
directions: Dump rigatoni into large pot.
Put all ingredients on rigatoni and mix until well blended.
Add your favorite tomato sauce to the rigatoni.

title: superb barbecue sauce
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, pepper, salt, cayenne, lemon juice, onion and butter.
Simmer, uncovered for 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: cheese crescents
directions: In medium bowl mix together flour, margarine, salt and 1/2 cup cottage cheese.
I find this works best when I mix with my hands. (There will still be small lumps from the cheese.)
Chill several hours up to several days.
Divide dough into thirds.
On lightly floured surface, roll each third into a 10-inch circle about 1/8-inch thick.
Mix well remaining 1/2 cup of cottage cheese and egg.
(Again, there will still be some lumps.)
Spread 1/3 of this mixture on each circle.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Starting from wide end, roll up each wedge.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake on top rack of preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes until golden. Remove to racks to cool.
Makes 24.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Finely chop the chicken.
In a small bowl stir together the soy sauce and pepper.
Set aside.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add the mayonnaise and water.
Bake at 350° until done about 30 minutes.
Test with a toothpick to see if it's done.
Makes an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: five-grain cereal loaf
directions: Stir together cereal and buttermilk and let stand 5 minutes. Add egg, sugar and vegetable oil, mixing well.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well.
Add to cereal mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes; a wooden pick inserted in center should come out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing.
Yields 15 servings.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper, milk and eggs; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in batter; set aside.
Pour oil into frying pan; heat to 350°.
Gently place chicken, skin side down, in skillet. Turn pieces of chicken over when beginning to brown.
When all pieces are lightly browned, reduce heat and cover.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 to 15 minutes more or until large pieces are easily pierced with fork.
Drain chicken on paper towels.

title: no fail custard pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and	beat well.
Pour into a 9-inch, unbaked pie shell.	Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: 3 cheese noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat, adding onion and chopped green pepper.
Drain. Add and mix together all other ingredients.
Pour in large casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: milwaukee rye bread
directions: Pour potato water in mixing bowl.
When lukewarm, add yeast dissolved in 1/4 cup of the lukewarm liquid.
Stir in rest of ingredients; knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in warm place until doubled.
Form into loaves; place in pans.
Let rise. When double its bulk, bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Brush top with water.

title: cheese corn bake
directions: Cook corn in salted water for 2 to 3 minutes (1/2 cream-style, 1/2 whole corn is a good combination).
Drain.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Note:
For hotter relish, increase number of hot Portugal peppers.

title: german potato cakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and puree.
Cover bottom of frying pan with oil.
Ladle mixture into hot oil.
Replace oil as needed.
Fry cakes until golden brown.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolks, sour cream and flour.
Add lemon juice and then fold in egg whites that have been beaten until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Butter pie plate well, coat with graham cracker crumbs.
Add filling and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cake in, open the oven door slightly, until cooled.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Place peppers in bottom of well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cheese evenly over peppers.
Pour eggs and garlic (mixed together) evenly over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Place chicken in the bottom of a cake pan or baking dish.
Pour the broth and soup over the chicken. Prepare stuffing; put the stuffing on top of the chicken and soup. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: recipe to kill roaches
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Shape into balls.
Put on foil, under appliances, in cabinets, under burners of stove or anywhere you see bugs.
It takes 3 or 4 days to kill bugs.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add eggs and fruit cocktail. Beat well and pour into greased and floured oblong pan (or Bundt pan). Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel apples.
Slice thin.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour, egg and spices until mixture looks like cornmeal. Put on top of apples.
Add water.
Cut up margarine on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until top of pie is brown and crusty.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: spam sandwich spread
directions: Mix together and place in hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
This can be frozen and baked later.
For microwave oven, wrap in Saran Wrap and bake 1 minute.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Form small balls of dough and roll in sugar mix.
In bottom of angel food cake pan, place raisins and nuts.
Then place layer of balls in greased angel food cake pan.
Add sprinkling of chopped nuts and raisins.
Add layer of balls, then raisins; repeat until pan is half full.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Invert pan so syrup will drain into cake for few minutes.
Remove bottom side up.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumb mixture and 1/2 stick margarine.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Combine crumb mixture with 1/2 stick margarine which has been melted.
Bake in 275° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and salt on medium heat until mixture comes to	a
boil
(rolling
boil).
Add	raw peanuts and cook until peanuts
change
color
and taste if done.	Remove from heat, stir in soda.
Mix quickly and pour or spread on greased cookie sheet. Not
too
thin.
Let
cool	and
break in small pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut mushrooms in half so they can be stuffed.
Mix the cooked and drained sausage with the cream cheese.
Stuff the mushrooms with mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 300° until warm.

title: mixed fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar.
Add ginger ale and water.
Serve with crushed ice.

title: bernice perry's dessert crescents(similar to old-timey butter rolls)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Roll or press to enlarge each.
Spread each with 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Roll up and place in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Combine half and half and vanilla and pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: hot chocolate drink mix
directions: Store ingredients in airtight container until ready to use. To drink, add mixture to hot water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the tacorito
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quick corn salad
directions: In a mixing bowl combine corn and celery.
For dressing, in a screw-top jar combine oil, sugar, vinegar, celery seed, dry mustard and onion powder.
Cover and shake well.
Pour dressing over corn mixture.
Mix until coated.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut the wings into 3 pieces and discard the wing tips.
Stir the wings into the sauce and let sit, refrigerated, for at least 3 hours.
Spread wings on a foil-lined baking sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn wings every 15 minutes.
They must be very brown, so bake longer, if necessary.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Drain butter beans and kidney beans.
Mix all ingredients together, (cut bacon into small pieces).
Bake 40-60 minutes at 350 or cook on stovetop, covered 25-30 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt oleo, cherry juice and marshmallows.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Add nuts, cherries, dates and pineapple.
Mix well. Press in pan. Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin, water and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Pour into 3 large loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat potatoes in their syrup until heated through.
Drain and mash.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crab in a medium bowl.
When very well blended, carefully fold in crabmeat, without breaking up large chunks.
Mold into cakes.
If desired, dip cakes in another egg and dredge through bread crumbs.
Brown in hot skillet with butter until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: mr. kenney's chicken
directions: Place boneless breasts in cooking dish with vegetables. Combine last 7 ingredients in blender and pour over vegetables. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 300°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Stir in milk and banana or fruit.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, soda and chopped nuts.

title: mango ice-cream
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a glass dish and freeze, tightly covered.
Alternatively, pour and freeze in popsicle molds.
Remove from freezer a half hour before cutting into pieces and serving.

title: antipasto
directions: Layer all of this in a large dish and spoon on dressing.

title: simple no boil frosting
directions: Put in bowl and mix.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Beat on high speed in electric beater until thick and add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Stays soft, but firm.

title: momma's corn pudding
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Heat dish in oven while preparing the corn pudding.
First add sugar and flour to the eggs, then the corn, then the milk.
Pour in heated casserole dish.
Cook for about 45 minutes to an hour or brown on top.
You can tell when it is done, looks like puddin'.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Brown meat with pepper and onion.
Cut the top off of the bread and remove the center of the bread, piece by piece.
Put the bread in a bowl.
Add Cheddar cheese soup to the meat and heat. Mix the bread pieces with the meat and soup until thick.
Pour the meat mixture inside the bread.
Place slices of Velveeta on top of meat and replace the top of the bread.
Wrap in foil and bake in oven 30 minutes at 350° or until heated and cheese has melted.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, oleo and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and coconut and pour over crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter and spread over the baked mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: relish
directions: Cook all together except flour until tender or about 20 minutes.
Keep out enough vinegar to stir in flour, add to the rest and cook until thick.
Put into jars and seal.

title: aunt jane's jelly cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Add
flour,
1/2	cup
at a time; mix.
Roll into balls and place
on greased cookie sheet.
Make an indentation in each cookie. Fill with jelly.
Bake about 8 minutes at 375° or until edges turn slightly golden.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Beat eggs until fluffy, then add sugar slowly and beat well.
Add oil, vanilla, zucchini and dry ingredients.
Blend together thoroughly and add nuts (if desired). Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans and bake about 1 hour.
Test for doneness with toothpick; if it comes out clean, the bread is done.

title: italian sausage subs
directions: Saute green pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except sausage and hot dog rolls.
Simmer.
Brown sausage; add to sauce.
Serve on hot dog rolls.

title: cracker candy
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place saltines on aluminum foil lined baking pan.
In small saucepan bring sugar and butter to a boil. Boil one minute.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake for 5 to 6 minutes or until bubbly all over.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let stand for 3 minutes until chocolate is melted.
Spread evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool.
Break into pieces and serve.

title: roasted lemon and soy sauce barbecue chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Mix soy sauce, lemon juice and white pepper.
Inject mixture into breast, thighs and other meaty parts, using baster with a needle end.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Boil tortellini for only
5 minutes.
Cool under cold water and drain.
Mix tortellini with all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove garlic cloves before serving.

title: vermont maple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add shortening, sugar, maple syrup and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 7 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli in 2-quart saucepan. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover with water. Cook until tender. Mash broccoli up, if desired, with potato masher. Add milk. Bring to a boil and add can of Cheddar cheese soup. Add a few slices of cheese, if desired. Add garlic or onion powder to taste. Mix flour with a little water to blend, then add to soup and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: my chile
directions: Using a large pot, brown the meat.
Add all spices, except garlic powder.
Stir.
After simmering for 1 to 2 minutes, generously sprinkle meat-spice mixture with ketchup and garlic powder.
Stir and continue to simmer.
Add the 2 cans of beans and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Continue at simmer for 2 hours.
Do not skimp on simmering.
This mixes the flavors.
For moisture, use beer during cooking as needed.
Serve with shredded Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese.

title: holiday buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Refrigerate; form small balls the size of buckeyes. Refrigerate.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip each ball 2/3 into chocolate with toothpick.
Let dry on waxed paper.
Refrigerate, if needed.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger until done.
Stir in Chili-O mix.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer over low heat.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper and beans.
Simmer.
If mixture is too thick, add water. Add desired cooked spaghetti and onions.

title: baked flavored turkey
directions: Wash and clean out turkey well, removing all insides.
Stuff inside of turkey with celery, onion, apples and other fruits, if desired.
Secure.
Place turkey in pan on rack.
Pour in bottom of pan approximately 1 inch of water and the white wine.
Top turkey with Wish-Bone Italian dressing, soy sauce, seasoning salt, pepper, paprika, parsley, garlic powder and oregano.
Loosely put foil on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: cauliflower gratin with chiles and cheese
directions: Remove large outer leaves and stalk of cauliflower.
Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Cover and cook in a small amount of boiling water 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain.

title: quick and easy pepper jelly appetizer
directions: Stir jelly in jar. Place cream cheese block on platter. Pour jelly over cheese (do not mix or stir). Serve with crackers.

title: beef and tomato stew
directions: Cut meat and veggies to bite-size pieces.
Add water (as much as needed).
Best cooked in slow cooker, about 5 hours on high. May cook on top of stove, 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Crush vanilla wafers and add with milk.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: waspers nest
directions: Cook pudding with milk until boiling and thick.
Add cake mix and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with the butterscotch morsels.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg well (if fatty, drain).
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for about an hour.

title: poor man's turkey
directions: Place meat in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Mix dressing and put on top.
Then add on top of mixture 2 cans cream of chicken soup, 1 can cream of celery soup and the chopped onion.
If bread is fresh, toast it!
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: oven steamed rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and bake until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, approximately 30 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend all in blender.
Sweet and colorful.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Beat eggs lightly in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients in order given. Pour into pie crust. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: tomato loaf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin
in
cold water.
Heat soup to boiling point and add cheese.
Add gelatin and beat until smooth.
Set aside to cool.
Add vegetables, nuts and mayo.
Pour into loaf tin and when firm, slice and serve on lettuce.
Can be made in small cupcake tins and unmold one on a lettuce leaf.

title: german cabbage
directions: Remove bacon and in some of the fryings, add the vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add the cabbage and onion; cook until tender.
Then add the crisp and crumbled bacon.
Simmer a while longer.
You may need to add water from time to time.
Serve in a dish with more crumbled bacon, if desired.

title: apple pound cake
directions: In bowl combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Beat thoroughly with mixer or by hand.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg, which have been mixed together, then gradually add the flour.
Fold in the nuts, coconut and apples.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken with the dressing for about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute green onions and mushrooms in vegetable oil. Pour on top of chicken patties.
Bake in oven for about 20 minutes. Remove and place slice of cheese on each patty.
Return to oven and bake about 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: homestyle potato chips
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut them into very thin slices.
Heat the shortening in a fryer to 365°.
Fry the slices for 5 to 8 minutes until they are golden brown.
Be careful not to try to fry too many potatoes at once.
Sprinkle with salt while they're hot.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water. Bring to a rolling boil. Stir in nuts gradually so as not to lose boil. Keep at a rolling boil until nuts turn a light brown. Remove from heat. Stir in soda and salt. Pour into well buttered pan or platter. Allow to spread on its own. Cool.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All with Cheez Whiz.
Stir in 1/2 oleo.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and spread the undrained crushed pineapple over the bottom of the pan; add the layer of blueberries and the 3/4 cup of sugar.
Sprinkle the box of cake mix on top of the fruit layers, then drizzle the melted butter all over the layer of dry cake mix.
Top with generous amount of pecans.

title: slightly different meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 20 minutes, then drain liquid from pan.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add sugar.
Grind cranberries and apples, then add to gelatin with the remaining ingredients.

title: pan fried fish
directions: Mix the ingredients on plate.
Coat washed and cleaned fish in mixture.
Heat butter and cooking oil in frying pan.
Cook fish until golden brown on medium heat.

title: hershey's kisses cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Add the egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; put Kisses on top.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: fast chicken and pasta soup
directions: Pour broth in crock-pot.
Add green onions.
Stir in pasta and can of chicken with broth.
Put frozen broccoli and carrots in a covered pan. Cook until soft (or microwave).
Add to crock-pot. Add milk.
For desired thickness, add milk, water or thickener. Add cheese. Slow cook as long as possible.
Ready to eat in 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together cold.
Pour over cukes.
Let stand for 2 days. They keep for 3 months in refrigerator.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 8-inch baking dish, place 3 tortillas overlapping slightly.

Layer 1/3 of tomatoes, chicken, scallions, chilies, olives, sour cream and cheese over tortillas. Cover with another 3 tortillas and layer half of remaining tomatoes, chicken, scallions, chilies, olives, sour cream and cheese.
Then repeat layers again, ending with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake, uncovered about 35 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread out crescent rolls flat on large cookie sheet, pinching seams together.
Press down, then bake as required on package. Blend cheeses, mayonnaise and dill together, then spread on cooled crescent crust.
Top with chopped veggies.

title: honey roasted nuts
directions: In a large microwave baking dish, stir together all ingredients.
Microwave on High (100%), stirring once, for 7 minutes.
Pour the nut mixture onto a sheet of foil and let cool. Break up nuts and store in cool cups.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, sour cream, soup, noodles and milk. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
On top of noodles and chicken mixture, spread broccoli.
Press down evenly.
Cover top of casserole with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly hot in middle.

title: homemade refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream Crisco shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add cold and boiling water, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Beat well.
Then gradually add remaining flour until well mixed.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Use as needed.

title: giant oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and spices; set aside.
Combine butter and sugar, creaming well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and add nuts, if desired.
Drop dough by 1/4 cup measure 5 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown the chili meat in large heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic; stir.
Cook together with meat, about 5 minutes.
Add can of tomato sauce and water.
Add can of tomato paste and water, together with cumin seed.
Add chili powder about 1 hour before done and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, covered, on stove or oven about 2 hours.
Remove cover and simmer until thickens.

title: 911 chili con carne with tomatoes
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except kidney beans.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally (or cook, uncovered, about 45 minutes).
Stir in beans; heat.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Makes 4 to 5 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add macaroni and cheese, soup and peas to ground beef.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in remaining ingredients except almonds and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: beef tacos
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and garlic; cook until tender. Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 cup cheese; stir until melted.
Place shells on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Fill shells with meat mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and remaining cheese.
Serve with sauce.
Makes 12 tacos.

title: meat puffs
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix all ingredients well. Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spray with cooking spray. Spoon mixture in heaping spoonfuls onto the aluminum foil. Bake in a preheated oven at 420° for 30 minutes. Makes about 5 or 6.

title: potato-broccoli bake
directions: Melt 2 teaspoons butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until bubbly.
Add cheeses; stir until melted.
Add potatoes.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Put a layer of broccoli. Add remaining potato mixture.
Cover and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli dressing
directions: Toss with broccoli and cauliflower tips.
Serve cold.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour; mix well.
Stir in water and evaporated milk and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Drain crabmeat; remove cartilage and flake crabmeat.
Add celery, pimento, pepper, hard-boiled eggs, salt and almonds.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with shredded cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Set aside.
Mix milk, egg yolks and butter. Bring to a boil.
Add flour mixture.
Cook until thick. Cool and pour into baked pie crust.
Use egg whites for topping.
Makes 1 pie.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake paper. Mix well the cream cheese and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Fill papers 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and mix with soup in a casserole dish.
Spread dried onions on top.
Bake at 350° until onions are golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in a large bowl the hash browns, soup, sour cream, onion, 1 stick melted margarine and cheese.
Mix well.
