Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dip dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl.
Cover hot dogs with mixture and drop in hot cooking oil until brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together. Mix the other ingredients and add to the first 3 items, alternating with buttermilk. Last, add Raisin Bran cereal. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: To cooked, drained spinach, add beaten eggs, melted butter and all spices and seasonings.
Add chopped onion; continue stirring well.
Lastly, add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and the stuffing crumbs.
Stir thoroughly.
Spoon into 6 to 8 medium, fresh tomatoes which have been hollowed and drained.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Slice and spread potatoes in a baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Place browned pork chops over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beef jerky
directions: Marinate the sliced meat in the sauces overnight.
Dry in a food dryer or a screen in the oven 200° or less, if possible. Brush with sauces while drying, 4 to 5 hours, depending on oven temperature.
My hunter's favorite!

title: potatoes
directions: Cook 20 more minutes (test potatoes for doneness).

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped walnuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.
Spread with confectioners sugar butter icing and sprinkle with shredded orange rind.
Decorate with whole walnuts, optional (no need to put frosting on or orange rind).
Can use oleo or Mazola instead of butter.

title: scones
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, ground nutmeg and salt and mix well.
Cube unsalted butter and work in with fingers until pea-sized pieces form.
Stir in raisins and sugar.
Whisk together egg yolk and buttermilk and stir into mixture.
Turn out dough onto floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Cut in half and pat each half into a 6-inch circle, slice circle into 6 wedges.
Transfer wedges in a circle to ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 18 to 22 minutes until lightly browned.

title: chocolate thin mint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Stir flour, cocoa, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture gradually, mixing at low speed, after each addition.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Press crumb mix and melted butter in 10 x 16-inch pan.
Cream soft butter.
Add icing sugar and 2 beaten eggs.
Beat until light.
Pour over crumbs.
Beat 1/2 pint whip cream.
Fold in pineapple.
Sprinkle with leftover crumbs.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: q m c - fruit salad
directions: Boil juice from pineapple.
Add Jell-O.
Let Jell-O set in refrigerator.
After jelling, add nuts, cherries, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold mixture.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: economic enchiladas
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, milk and green chilies.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Line casserole dish with one layer of corn tortillas.
Spread half of soup mixture over tortillas, sprinkle half of the cheese over mixture.
Repeat with remaining ingredients and top with sliced olives.
Heat at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 cups boiling water.
Combine sugar and 4 cups cold water.
Bring to a boil until sugar dissolves.
Add to gelatin and cool.
When cool, add lemon and pineapple juices.
Mix well.
Pour into containers suitable for freezing.
Freeze.
Take out several hours before time to use.
(Should be slushy.)
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (not oil) 13 x 9-inch pan. (Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.)
In large bowl, blend all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a coffee urn.
Serve hot. Yield: 30 servings.

title: crunchy crust french toast
directions: Blend egg, milk, sugar and cinnamon. Mix coconut and corn flakes.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture and then coat with coconut mixture.
Heat margarine in a skillet over medium heat. Brown prepared bread slices in skillet until light golden on both sides.
If desired, serve with additional margarine and maple syrup.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix the tomatoes, lettuce, radishes and cucumbers.
Add the cheese, broken into small pieces, and the cut up olives.
Toss with the dressing.

title: fruit and cheese appetizer
directions: On a cocktail toothpick, string pineapple tidbits, maraschino cherry halves, cubed cheese and grapes.
Place on a pretty tray. These are easily made and are usually the first to disappear.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Skin and wash chicken pieces.
Cover with salted water and soak for 45 minutes.
Place thighs in dish; season and cover. Place in microwave on High for 8 minutes, then turn 1/2 turn. Then set at High for 8 minutes again.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Whip eggs and almond extract together.
Add cake mix and cherries.
Mix until moist.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice celery skillet
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and rice in margarine for 3 minutes or until onion is almost tender and rice is lightly browned.
Add celery and saute 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour and measure and sift with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch.
Cook dates, water and white sugar over low heat about 5 minutes.
Avoid scorching.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add nuts.
Spread filling on cookie dough and roll as a jelly roll.
Chill 1 hour.
Slice and bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix melted margarine with the cookie crumbs; press 1/2 of cookie crumb mix into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish for a crust. Cut softened ice cream into inch slices and place on crumb crust. Drizzle your favorite topping on the ice cream, then spread Cool Whip over topping.
Sprinkle rest of cookie crumb mix on top; add chopped nuts, if desired.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan. Cool.
Beat eggs and sugar until pale yellow. Add the cooled chocolate; stir well. Add flour and salt; blend until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan, greased and floured on the bottom only. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: lemon ice
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon peel and juice.
Cool to room temperature.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and salt.
Add bananas and flour mixture (flour, baking powder and soda) alternately.
Bake in lightly greased and floured loaf pans in a 325` oven for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in sheet pan.
Combine milk and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Poke holes in cake with fork, large tong.
Pour milk and sugar over cake.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well except butter.
Put on floured board and knead a few minutes.
Roll or pat out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter and fold.
Place in pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° until done.
Yields 18 to 20 rolls.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onions; drain. Add all other ingredients, except cheese and chips. Pour into a casserole dish; top with cheese and place crushed Doritos on top. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey supreme casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together except cheese and chips.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Place next 3 ingredients in separate bowl to dissolve.
Add 2 cups flour to butter mixture; blend.
Then add the eggs, yeast mixture, salt, then the rest of the flour.
Dough will be slightly sticky.
Let the dough rise in a dry, warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch the dough down and let rise for 45 minutes more.
Then form.
Roll out enough dough to make a 12 x 16-inch rectangle.
Spread soft butter on entire face of dough.
Then sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top of butter.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and oleo.
Add peanut butter and eggs. Mix until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls or make large balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet. Put a few M&M's on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place oil in casserole. Cut up potatoes; place in oil. Salt, pepper and Creole season to taste. Mix in oil until coated. Place onion and bell pepper strips on top of potatoes. Slice sausage and place on top. Cover
with shredded cheese. Bake until potatoes are done at 375°.

title: no-bake pound cake
directions: In double boiler heat milk;
add marshmallows and melt. When melted,
add
pecans, raisins and crushed vanilla wafers. Mix together good
with
hands.
(Keep hands greased good with margarine while mixing.) Put cake in loaf pan and refrigerate. Slice thin when cool.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease or spray 9 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle the coconut and pecans on the bottom of the dish.
Prepare the cake mix according to the directions.
Pour the cake mix over coconut and pecans.
Microwave the cream cheese and margarine on 80% power until melted.
Add one box of confectioners sugar and mix well. Pour this over the cake mix.
Bake about 55 minutes at 350°.
May sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken medley
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions on package.
Set aside.
Next melt the margarine and add the flour.
Blend and add the chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
To this mixture, add the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and sprinkle of curry.
Mix together with the stuffing to make the first layer.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients in container of electric ice cream freezer.
Add ice and salt to freezer; freeze 15 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Mix together well and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hominy grits casserole
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 1 minute; stir.
Melt together both cheeses and margarine.
Add eggs.
Add to grits and melted cheese. Pour these into large casserole (I use 9 x 13-inch pan).
Put crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pina colada
directions: Blend with crushed ice.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix well and let set 24 hours.
Just before serving, add Fritos corn chips.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortenings.
Add eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Follow these steps carefully!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle sugar on top.
Add grated Cheddar cheese or crisp diced bacon for garnish.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease 11 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut on bottom; pour in batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine bread, cheese and sausage and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hazelnut cakes(makes 12 to 14 small cakes)
directions: Boil the ground nuts in the water, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes or until the mixture is the consistency of mush.
Mix in the corn meal and salt and let stand for about 20 minutes or until thick.

title: apple pie deluxe
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix with the apples.
In a
9-inch
pie
pan place bottom crust.
Fill with the apple mixture
and
sprinkle
butter
over
apple mixture. Brown sugar may
be
used
instead of granulated.
Add the top crust and with a fork, insert a few holes.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for
15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to moderate oven at 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine in a lightly greased souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve with warm thin slices of French bread, corn chips, tortilla chips, Melba toast, etc.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust for 10 minutes at 400°.
Slice tomatoes thick and layer in pie crust.
Sprinkle with salt, basil, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Put on top of sliced tomatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, garlic powder and pepper in large pan, then drain off grease.
Add 1 large and small can of tomato sauce and 1 large economy size McCormick spaghetti sauce mix; set aside. Boil noodles and drain.
Put layer of noodles then layer of meat. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then cover with Mozzarella cheese and then cover with American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate raisin bars
directions: Place raisins in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar in a saucepan; cook and stir to hard ball stage (254°).
Pour over raisins.
Top with chocolate pieces.
Chill until firm.

title: luxury chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate bits in double boiler.
Cool completely at room temperature.
While this is cooling, cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate bits.
Beat until smooth.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring macaroni to boil, then drain.
Add cheese and cream (not milk), then add other ingredients.
Mix well; bake at 350° until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and let stand 1/2 hour.
Grind orange and apple; add to the celery and nuts.
Mix jello and allow to cool but not set.
(Allow for juice that forms on fruit when adding water to jello.)

title: denver sandwich ring
directions: Mix Bisquick, oil, milk and egg, then add other ingredients. Drip from tablespoon
on
greased
cookie
sheet to form circle. Bake 15 to	20
minutes
at
425°.	Serve
with cheese sauce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces and place in bottom of large bowl.
Mix together milk, confectioners sugar, sour cream and Cool Whip and pour over cake.
Mix slightly.
Mix together the glaze and strawberries with juice; pour over cake mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with salad dressing and sugar. Fold in whipped cream, fruit cocktail and marshmallows.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Add 7-Up or Sprite at time of serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion for 5 minutes in salted water. Drain.
Combine soup, carrots and sour cream; fold into drained squash.
Set aside.
Combine and mix melted margarine and stuffing.
Spread half the stuffing in large casserole dish.
Add vegetable mixture; cover with remaining stuffing, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stove top cheese fondue
directions: Cut crusts from bread and cut bread in 1/4-inch cubes.
Put in top of double boiler.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put over hot water until cheese melts and mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Beat in egg and butter and cook, stirring, about 5 minutes.
Serve on toast with sprinkling of paprika.
Serves 6.

title: rice and green chile casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Butter casserole dish.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover 1/2 the time.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage and drain good (crumble).
Mix sausage and cheese together in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie shell with sausage.
Run a fork through mixture and mix together.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cook cake according to box directions.

title: hot spicy cider
directions: In pot, mix cider
or juice, sugar and spices and bring to a boil.
Reduce
heat;
simmer
10 minutes.
Stir in orange peel. Serve hot.	Serves 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon
together in large mixing bowl. Then add oil, eggs and carrots. Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° about 30 or 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: oriental salad
directions: Saute sunflower seeds, almonds and 2 packages noodles in oleo. Watch so they don't burn.

title: canadian bacon pita pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut Canadian-style bacon into 1/2-inch strips and set aside.
Place onion in 1-quart microwave-safe container.
Cover.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Place pita bread, smooth side up, on baking sheets.
Top each pita with equal amounts of onion, bacon and roasted pepper. Sprinkle with equal amounts of cheese and olives.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until pitas are crisp.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Heat sugar and white syrup until it starts to bubble. Add peanut butter. Stir in.
Add mixture to 6 cups Rice Krispies.
Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt both kinds of chips together and spread over bars.

title: ham with honey-butter sandwich
directions: Mix together butter, honey, mustard and soy sauce.
Spread on bread, top with ham and other slice of bread.

title: doodle bean dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with Fritos.

title: plain and pleasing
directions: Pat out four patties of equal size.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place in oven and broil 10 minutes on each side.
Mix gravy by package directions and pour over patties.
Place onion and potato slices over patties.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Place back in oven and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: herb-grilled chicken
directions: In a bowl, mix oil, cider vinegar, eggs, flour, salt, poultry seasoning, pepper, oregano, garlic powder and paprika.
Brush on all sides of chicken.
Place chicken on prepared grill, skin side up, 6 inches from heat.
Grill for about 45 minutes, turning and basting with sauce every 15 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients, tossing well.
Serve immediately or if desired, chill.

title: deviled seafood
directions: Stir together all ingredients until blended.
Spoon into a 1-quart shallow casserole or 8 inch ovenproof shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli and cauliflower.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble over broccoli and cauliflower.
Chop onion.
Add onion, raisins and peanuts to broccoli and cauliflower.
This can be kept in refrigerator overnight.

title: sugar-glazed ham
directions: Score ham about 1/2 inch deep with a sharp knife.
Place ham on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours (20 minutes per pound).
Combine brown sugar, mustard and enough vinegar to make a thick paste.
During the last hour of baking, brush glaze on ham every 15 minutes.
Yields 10 to 14 servings.

title: mixed spicy rib with juice
directions: Rinse ribs.
Cut in short.
Take 2/3 head lemon to make juice and 1/3 for slice as garnish.
Rinse tomato; slice as garnish. Blend lemon juice, hashed peel into rib.
Pour marinade to stir for 20 minutes.
Drain ribs.
Sprinkle flour to coat thoroughly.
Heat wok half full with oil; deep fry ribs until done.
Remove and dish up.
Garnish with tomato and fresh lemon.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Reserve 1/4 cup grease.
Add vinegar and sugar to grease.
Heat on medium until sugar is dissolved, stir constantly.
Place green beans in bottom of casserole.
Place onion rings on top.
Sprinkle with bacon and pour vinegar mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Best when prepared 1 day ahead.

title: jungle breakfast
directions: Before girls wake up, hang items from trees.
When they ask, "What's for breakfast?" tell them a "Jungle Breakfast, you go and find it."
Girls have to find one of each item.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except raspberries.
Mix until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup for the topping.
Press dough into 9 x 13 pan.
Cover dough with jam or preserves.
Take the 1 cup of crumb mixture and add 2 tablespoons flour to make more crumbly. Crumble on top of jam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into bars.

title: real italian lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add next 8 ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.
Make white sauce (about 3 cups medium consistency). Cook lasagne noodles.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish in this order: noodles, white sauce, meat sauce, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and separate flowerets.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir together next 3 ingredients.
Pour over one hour before serving. Refrigerate until served.

title: mom's southern bread pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs well and add to the sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix and pour into buttered Pyrex dish.
Top with the bread crumbs.
Push the bread down into mixture until it is coated.
It will float to form a crust.
Bake at 350° until the pudding thickens.
Then broil until crust turns very light brown.

title: pecan coconut pie
directions: Put butter, eggs, sugar and vinegar in double boiler over hot water until butter melts.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until brown and firm.

title: quick hearty vegetable soup
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, lightly brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Cream potatoes with Crisco.
Add eggs, salt and sugar.
Scald milk and cool.
Mix yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Add to milk, then add all to potato mixture.
Add 6 to 8 cups of sifted, plain flour.
Pour out on board and knead well.
Put in greased bowl. (Note:
After greased on one side, turn over and grease other side.)
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead lightly on board. Put back into greased bowl and place in refrigerator overnight. Will last several days.
Place damp cloth on top to keep from crusting.
Take out dough and knead enough to roll out (about like biscuits).
Set in warm place and let rise about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Bake.
Butter tops when done.
Delicious!

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Mix bread as directed to the point it is ready to make into rolls.
Remove casing from pepperoni and cut into 4 equal-sized pieces, then quarter each piece into strips.
Wrap bread dough around each piece and place on greased cookie sheet, grease tops, cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave dough ornaments
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir soda, cornstarch and water together. Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until thick.
Cool.
Use immediately or store in plastic bag in refrigerator until used.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put on bottom of pie dish sprayed with Pam. Boil water, vanilla, gelatin, coconut extract, lemon juice and cinnamon for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over pineapple.

title: amber's favorite lasagna
directions: Heat oils.
Add beef, onion, and garlic; brown for 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, sauce, sugar, salt, basil, 1/2 cup parmesan cheese and pepper.
Mix well, bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Mix ricotta and mozzarella with egg, set aside.
Cook noodles.
Put a thin layer of sauce in 9 x 13 pan, a layer of noodles, then the cheese-egg mixture.
Make 3 layers.
On top layer add 1/4 cup parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: good pancake syrup
directions: Put ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, then remove from heat.
Serve hot or cold.
This doesn't need refrigeration.

title: scallops with shrimp and artichokes
directions: If scallops are large, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place scallops in a 2-quart saucepan; add just enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes, or until scallops are white; drain.
Keep scallops warm.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies for crust, reserving 1/2 cup for topping.
Pour melted butter over cookies and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding (by directions on box) and spread over crust. Beat the cream cheese and confectioners sugar together; blend in 3/4 container of Cool Whip.
Spread over pudding.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top of cake; sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine beans, seasoning mix, cream cheese, sour cream, Tabasco sauce and garlic in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Spoon into small baking dish.
Top with cheese, tomatoes and olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon twist and parsley, if desired.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.
Bake a 350 for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and spread on icing.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add sauce and tomatoes; mix.
Place chips in bottom of large casserole dish.
Pour meat sauce over chips.
Top with beans and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and salt.
Stir constantly until clear.
Add jello powder and mix well.
Cool; pour over strawberries in a prebaked crust.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat with wooden spoon.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve 1 package plain gelatin in a little water and add orange jello.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and stir.
Set aside to cool.
Put whole cranberry sauce and pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan with lid and mix.
Pour jello mixture in and mix well.
Add some chopped black walnuts and place in refrigerator until set. This keeps well in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour round steak and place in 2 tablespoons of oil in slow cooker on high setting.
Add tomatoes, onions and green peppers along with 1 to 1 1/2 cups water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 4 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes own gravy.
Serves 4.

title: brownie cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and smooth.
Add vanilla and cocoa.
Add flour mixture.
Add nuts.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Pour all ingredients into medium-size mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Drop by tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
(Pam is great to use.)
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Oven times may vary.
Great to use when having additional guests for dinner.

title: mandarin orange jello-sherbet mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sherbet, stirring until it melts completely.
Let stand in mold or Bundt pan until it starts to thicken (in refrigerator).
Add well drained fruit. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: sunshine brunch punch
directions: Combine juice and ginger ale in a punch bowl.
Top with scoops of sherbet.
Garnish with mint leaves, if desired.
Yields 26 four-ounce servings.

title: creamed pork chops
directions: Wipe pork chops with damp paper towels.
Brown them in a little heated oil. Arrange chops in oiled baking dish.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares and garnish with Cool Whip and a cherry.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Take 2 cups of kindness, 1 cup of consideration and stir in a large measure of thoughtfulness.
Add 1 cup humor, kind regards and fondness.
Beat until smooth with comfort and real caring. Dissolve with neighborliness, tenderness and devotion.
Never mince kind words.
Blend with lots of affection and love.
Simmer at an even temperature.
This recipe will ensure sweet friendship and a happy heart.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill unopened can of milk in freezing compartment until icy (about 3 hours).
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until light and fluffy. Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk and fold into gelatin mixture. Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan with vanilla wafer crumbs. Pour in the gelatin/milk mixture and top with remaining crumbs.

title: chopstick chicken
directions: Combine soup, broth, half of the noodles, chicken, celery, onion and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining noodles and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans; in 5-quart pan, combine beans and 6 cups water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover, let stand 1 hour, drain.
Add 8 cups water, ham shank, onions, parsley, salt, basil, pepper, nutmeg, garlic, oregano and bay leaf to beans.
Bring to boil, reduce heat; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat.
Remove meat, take from bone.
Return meat to soup; stir in carrots, celery and potato flakes until blended.
Return to heat; simmer covered for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: judy's tuna casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top off casserole with buttered bread crumbs.
Serves 4 people.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes (instant or regular, hot and seasoned to taste).
Brown hamburger and onion, then pour off excess grease.
Add ketchup to the hamburger and stir.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with mashed potatoes to form a pie shell.
Pour hamburger mixture into potato shell and top with slices of American cheese. Bake in oven at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is thoroughly melted.
Cut and serve as you would a pie.

title: springtime casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes. (May substitute wieners or Polish sausage for ham.) Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple streusel dessert
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch pan generously with butter.
Place apples in rows as close as possible!
Mix white sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour, brown sugar and butter together until crumbly. Sprinkle over and between apples.
Pat surface flat.
Bake at 425° for 1/2 hour or until apples are tender. Serve with ice cream or hard sauce.

title: buttered turnips
directions: Here's something that goes fine with game dishes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Whip chilled Milnot until very stiff.
Mix cream cheese plus 1 cup of sugar.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water. Add everything together except vanilla wafers and butter.
Crumble vanilla wafers and mix with butter.
Put layer of crumbled wafers on bottom, then cheese mixture in middle and wafers on top.
Chill.

title: emily waller's hot chicken salad(a winner)
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Combine with rice, soup, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix well, but gently.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole. Coat top with additional corn flakes.
Bake 40 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: drunken sausage
directions: Cook sausage according to package directions, then slice. Combine brown sugar, sauce and bourbon in Dutch oven.
Add sausage.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring often.
Place in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: baked brie
directions: Place unwrapped Brie on baking sheet.
Smear with marmalade over the top.
Cover and sprinkle generously with currants.
Layer cover with slivered almonds on top.
Bake in 375° oven until puffy (20 minutes).
Serve with French bread, apples, grapes, crackers, etc.

title: cold green bean and onion salad
directions: Layer green beans and onion in serving dish.
Bring rest of ingredients to boil and pour over vegetables.
Cool and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt together in double boiler everything, except the cake mix.
While this is melting, mix the cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour the melted caramel mixture over the cake.
Then pour and spread rest of cake batter on top.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes more.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all water from spinach.
Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers, chips or veggies.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Combine and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Partially defrost hash browns.
Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, cheese, onions, sour cream, soup and spices.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top of potatoes.
Pour the 1/4 cup margarine over corn flakes.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: herbed cheese log
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in pimentos and olives.
When firm enough to handle, shape into ball or log.
Roll in
parsley.
Then chill until 1/2 hour before serving time.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux with olive oil and flour.
Cook garlic until light brown.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add shrimp, tomato paste and water.
Mix well.
Add all ingredients except okra and oysters.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add okra and cook 15 minutes.
Add oysters, cook another 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: wine punch
directions: In a gallon container combine first 4 ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Stir in cherries.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve chilled.
Makes about 3 quarts punch.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: A 6-quart pressure cooker is needed.

title: bavarian mint coffee creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients in container. Shake to blend well. Makes 15 servings.
Use 2 tablespoons per 16 ounces coffee.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Beat well the eggs (3 or 4 minutes).
Add graham crackers and sugar and baking powder (sifted together).
Add chopped nuts. Grease pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 2 sticks of butter, and Velveeta cheese in microwave. Pour over broccoli that has been placed in casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with crushed crackers.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Bring first five ingredients together to boil and cook 4 minutes or until berries break and color turns blue.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Cool slightly.
Then add 3 to 4 cups raw blueberries and gently fold in.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill for several hours.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper; cook until thick.
Stir in cream and broth.
Cook until hot.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Make syrup out of water, sugar and candy.
Cook apples in syrup until uniform in color.
Chill and stuff with cream cheese mixture (one 3 ounce package cream cheese, 1 teaspoon salad dressing and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts).

title: macaroni twist salad
directions: Cook macaroni twist as directed on package.
Drain; rinse in cold water until cool.
Add vegetables; can use any kind that you like best.
Fresh, frozen or canned.
Can use any meats you like best:
ham, turkey or chicken.
Keep refrigerated until used.
Put boiled eggs on top.

title: cheesed chicken and asparagus
directions: Brown chicken breasts in shortening or butter (doesn't take too long).
Sprinkle with a bit of garlic powder and paprika, if desired.
Place chicken breasts in long casserole dish.
Sprinkle mushrooms all over.
Mix together the soups and thyme.
Arrange asparagus spears in a long row over the top of mushrooms.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Good served with warmed spiced peaches and chicken or herbed rice.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prick pie shell with fork, bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Reduce oven to 325°. Beat the eggs, cream, milk, salt and hot pepper sauce together.
Spread the cheese over the bottom of the pie shell; pour in the egg mixture and bake 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: chicken divine
directions: Fill a pot with 6 or 7 cups of water and bring to boil. Place the chicken into the boiling water and cook until done (approx. 10-12 minutes depending on size). Remove chicken and place into a 9x13 inch pan. Place the broccoli on top of the chicken. Mix the soup and mayo together and pour over the chicken and broccoli. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes to heat through. Then remove from oven and top with cheese. Place back in the oven for 5 or 6 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix all but cocktail sauce together.
Shape as desired.
Pour cocktail sauce on top and serve with crackers.
Pour extra cocktail sauce on top as needed.
Chill until ready to use.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix vegetables together and set aside. Over low heat, mix together the vinegar, sugar, salad oil and salt. Pour over vegetables. Cover and chill.

title: tiny's biscuitsdallas, texas
directions: Mix the ingredients with your hands.
Add approximately 1 1/2 c. buttermilk, to be sticky moist.
Put on floured wax paper, roll in your hands.
Place on a hot, greased heavy pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, mix sugar, margarine, evaporated milk and salt.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add chocolate chips, marshmallows, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour quickly into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until ready to cut.

title: cornish game hens au vinaigre
directions: Sprinkle the cavity of the hens with salt and pepper.
Truss and rub the outside with salt and pepper.
Heat butter or oil in a heavy casserole with a cover.
Add game hens and brown all over for about 15 minutes.
Add giblets and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add mushrooms and garlic and cook briefly before adding onion.
Cook onion for 5 minutes and then add bay leaf and thyme.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add vinegar and broth and cook for 10 minutes, covered.
Untruss the birds and drain the cavity juices back into pan.
Discard garlic and bay leaf.
Serve hens hot with mushrooms and hot pan juices.

title: grandma helen's stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute chopped onion in a little oil with red paprika.
Wash rice and drain.
Mix meat with rice, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Steam cabbage leaves and peel off as they get soft.
Trim the outer vein for easier rolling.
Roll a small amount of meat mixture into each cabbage leaf.
Stack the rolls into a large pot.
Pour in the sauerkraut and tomato sauce.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil. Cook 1 hour at low with top on it.
Stir periodically.
Garnish each serving with sour cream.

title: nippy squares
directions: Beat eggs with cheese
and
peppers in bowl.
Pour into well greased 9-inch square baking
dish.
Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm and
light
golden brown.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Serve warm on toothpicks.	Serves 40.

title: raisin meringue pie
directions: Cook raisins in a small amount of water until tender.
Combine slightly beaten egg yolks, sugar, flour and margarine.
Pour egg mixture into raisins.
Cook until thick.
Pour into pastry shell. Cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until brown.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients in a medium-sized bowl. Pour oil into measuring cup. Add milk, but do not stir. Then pour all at once into the flour. Stir with fork until mixture clears sides of bowl and rounds up into a ball. For rolled or patted biscuits, smooth up, kneading 10 times with no additional flour. With dough on waxed paper, press out 1/4-inch thick with hands or roll out between waxed paper. Cut with unfloured biscuit cutter. Bake at 475° for 10-12 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: homemade mustard
directions: In a small bowl stir together 1/4 cup dry mustard and 2 tablespoons water; set aside.
In 1-quart saucepan mix well 2/3 cup water, cider vinegar, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook over low heat about 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in mustard mixture until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 1 cup.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Recipe may be doubled.
You can also add any other fruit or pie filling you like.

title: chicken and sweet sausage gumbo
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a large stock pot or kettle. Add sliced okra and cook, stirring constantly, 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender and lightly browned.
Remove from pot and set aside.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice in casserole dish.
Brown pork chop on each side. Not done, but brown.
Place on rice.
Pour consomme over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet - & - sour pork stir fry
directions: Dredge pork in cornstarch. Heat 2 Tbsp oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat; stir-fry pork in batches, 3 minutes or until browned. Remove pork from skillet; set aside.

title: devil's food fudge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine cake mix, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended. Stir in chips and walnuts.
Shape dough into 36 (1 1/4-inch) balls.
Place 2 inches apart on pans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove to cooling racks.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion.
Pack in jars and pour solution over pickles.
Put in refrigerator and keep until ready to use. Keeps all winter.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in a large baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix soups, water and oleo.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Microwave chocoloate and margarine in large bowl.
On high for 2 min., until margarine is melted.
Stir chocolate until melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Spread into greased 13x9-inch pan.
Bake 30-35 min.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 24 fudgy brownies.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix together 1 cup Mozzarella, Ricotta, salt, Parmesan, pepper and nutmeg. Cook large shells as directed on box and drain. Stuff each shell with cheese mixture. Pour 16 ounces sauce into bottom of a 9 x 13 casserole pan. Place stuffed shells into pan. Pour the rest of sauce over the top. Sprinkle the rest of Mozzarella cheese over the top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Mix all ingredients, putting in the hash browns last.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan and top with 2 cups crushed
cornflakes
mixed	with
cup melted butter. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain off any fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Top with dollop of sour cream on each serving if desired.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Mix together eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Add fruit juices and cook until thick.
Pour over macaroni and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip, fruit cocktail, pineapple and cherries.

title: mccall's casserole
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, layer rice, then corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour on 1 cup tomato sauce mixed with 1/2 cup water.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, including nuts if using.
In a separate bowl mix together eggs, oil and the zucchini.
Then add to the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two mid-sized greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple egg scramble
directions: Saute apple in skillet (sprayed with nonstick spray or oleo, melted) until soft.
Add bread, beaten egg and spices.
Brown over low heat until egg is cooked through.
Can be increased easily.

title: potato-onion soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add cream and reheat.
Can add 1 cup cooked, crumbled bacon for a different flavor.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and strain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, if desired.
Be sure to press out excess liquid from sauerkraut, then place sauerkraut over chicken. Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese. Cover with foil and bake in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours (or until chicken is done).
May sprinkle with 1 tablespoon parsley, chopped, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup butter until smooth; shape into a ball, wrap and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: twinkies delight
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise.
Line pan with cream side up.
Slice bananas.
Fix pudding mix.
Add crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Top with cherries or toasted coconut if desired.

title: chickpea dip(hummus)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and stop every minute.
Blend until smooth.
With a spatula, push mixture toward the blade to be sure that all the chickpeas are crushed.
Top with 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Decorate with chopped parsley and paprika and serve with Arabic bread, crackers or celery sticks.

title: simple roast turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a 19 x 24-inch oven cooking bag.
Place in 2-inch deep roasting pan.
Place vegetables in bag.
Rinse turkey well with cold water; remove neck and giblets and pat dry.
Brush turkey with oil; place in bag.
Close with tie.
Make 6 slits in top of bag.
Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thigh.
Bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or to 180°.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes before carving.

title: royal frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar and water; boil for 12 minutes.
Cool; add apricots, bananas, pineapple, strawberries, salt and nuts.
Pour into molds; freeze.
Serve partially frozen.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: sinful salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool, but not set. Thaw and drain the strawberries. Drain the can of pineapple well. Mash the bananas.
Add berries, pineapple and bananas to jello. Pour half of this mix into a 12 x 8-inch pan and place in fridge to set.
Leave other half at room temperature so it won't set.

title: honey gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add and blend in sugar.
Beat in honey and eggs until mixture is light.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add to honey mixture alternately with hot water.
Pour into a greased 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: hershey dessert
directions: Melt bars in double boiler; add egg yolks, beaten fine.
Whip together until cool.
Then add beaten whites and Cool Whip.
Add mixture slowly.
Then place layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of baking dish, repeat in layers, sprinkle nuts on top and refrigerate.
Very, very rich.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Combine all ingredients (except cheese) thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until half done.
Sprinkle cheese on top and finish baking.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Ladle pancake batter onto medium to hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles form on pancake.
Serve. Yields 6 cups, 24 pancakes.

title: cheese ball - quick and easy
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and 1/2 cup nuts together. Form into a ball, then roll ball in the rest of nuts.
Make a day ahead of time and store in refrigerator.

title: better-than-sex cake(makes 16 servings.)
directions: This recipe is a slimmed-down version of a very rich cake that appeared in Hope Health Letter.
The original had 405 calories and 26 grams fat per slice.
This version 270 calories and 10 grams fat.

title: mom's concoction
directions: In saucepan cook green pepper, celery, tomatoes and onion in pineapple juice.
Add cooked chicken chunks and pineapple pieces. Stir in water and taco seasoning.
Heat through, cover and simmer until cooked, stir fairly frequently.
Add more water if necessary.
Serve as you would regular tacos.
Use cheese, sour cream, olives and salsa as extras with the meat filling in the shells.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients; bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup cereal, water and salad oil; mix well.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt, soda, sugar and remaining 2 cups cereal.
Add eggs and buttermilk to flour mixture.
Mix well. Stir in cereal/oil mixture.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with butter crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend ingredients 2 minutes on medium speed.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tuna italiano
directions: Combine cheese, tuna, onion, tomatoes and celery in large bowl.
Mix next 6 ingredients in small screw-top jar.
Pour over tuna mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, cut pitas in half, fill and enjoy.

title: strawberry cool-its
directions: Mix first three ingredients together, then fill shells.
Top each with a fresh strawberry.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, beat pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add eggs; mix well. Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture and beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Cool

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an oblong pan.
Place cherry pie filling and pineapple in pan.
Mix well. Dump the box of cake mix on top of the cherries (dry cake mix).
Slice butter and place in chunks on top of cake mix. Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: cheddar cheese dip
directions: Make sure cream cheese and cheddar cheese are soft before starting.
Cut off an end of the bread and hollow out center, saving all pieces.
Mix together all other ingredients and put in hollowed-out bread.
Place end back on bread and serve.
Break off pieces of bread and dip in cheese mixture.
As pieces are used up, break up end of bread and sides of loaf to dip in cheese.

title: aunt molly's pumpkin soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
Add flour and curry; stir.
Gradually add broth.
Add all other ingredients, except the milk, and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add milk and heat without boiling.

title: quick pastry shell
directions: Stir until a ball of dough forms.
Press into pie pan.
Use as crust for quiche, etc.

title: sloppy joe casserole(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.

title: olive salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator as long as you would like to keep it.
Goes good with meat dishes.
Use brick form Parmesan cheese.
(Can be found in most stores with the other type cheeses, usually found on the shelves above the butter.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve hot! Delicious.

title: milky way chocolate cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick butter in double boiler.
Let cool.
Cream together the sugar and 2 sticks butter.
Add remaining ingredients to the creamed mixture, mixing until smooth. Add candy mixture last.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onions; drain.
Combine sausage, onions and other ingredients; mix well and chill overnight.
Shape into balls; roll in flour, then dip in beaten eggs, then roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: carameled sweet potatoes
directions: Cook
potatoes	until
tender.	Drain and cool.
Cut in half lengthwise and arrange in greased baking dish.
Mix salt, sugar and flour and pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Add marshmallows and
nuts
and pour cream over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: happy day cake
directions: Mix shortening in bowl. Add dry ingredients
sifted together. Add milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Then add eggs already beaten.
Beat 1 more minute. Pour in greased and floured pans. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes for round pans or 35 minutes for 9 x 13 pan.

title: almond snowdrifts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold salt, vanilla, almonds and flour into egg white mixture; blend well.

title: texas best onion rings
directions: Mix beer and flour with fork or wire whip.
Cover tightly; let stand for at least 4 hours.
It won't hurt to leave it all day. Peel onions; slice crosswise in 3/8-inch slices.
Drain.
Heat oil for frying.
Dip drained onion ring in batter and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
(These may be frozen and reheated at a later time if properly wrapped.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramels
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a hard boil.
Add butter, 1 cube at a time.
Stir constantly.
Add milk and cream alternately.
Boil to 225°.
Add vanilla and pour onto greased jelly roll pan.
Let cool for several hours and cut into squares.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and sugar together.
Add flour, eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: beans galore(sweet and sour)
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Set aside and drain.
In bacon grease, combine next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Add to bean mixture in a large, deep casserole.
Bake about 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: marilyn's chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; sprinkle with soda.
Cool.
Mix together the margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs and add to cooled date mixture.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; batter will be thin.
Sprinkle with topping made from chocolate chips, chopped nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna potato chip casserole
directions: Empty soup into small casserole dish.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Add tuna, 1/2 cup crushed potato chips, peas and macaroni to soup, stirring well.
Sprinkle the top with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pinto beans with kielbasa
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover and simmer until heated through.

title: dropped filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk, soda and flour.
Drop by teaspoonful 3 inches apart.
Add 1/2 teaspoon filling and drop another teaspoon of dough on top.
Do not press down too hard.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen or so. You can use apricot or grape jelly, cherry pie filling or raisins are very good.
Also strawberry jelly makes a good cookie.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend all together and put in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "perky popcorn"
directions: Patty sausage is recommended.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: In 2-quart baking pan, combine frozen corn, cream-style corn, cornbread mix, eggs, chilies, butter and pepper. Stir gently until combined. Place spoonfuls of sour cream on top of mixture. Fold in gently. Sprinkle the cheese over the top. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and pepper to taste. Drain meat. Add all ingredients together in large pot. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes and it is ready to eat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Blend in eggs, oil and carrots.
Put batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost with following icing.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Cut off mushroom stems even with caps.
(Use stems for soup or sauce or discard.)
Peel if skin is discolored.
Slice very large mushrooms.
Leave small ones whole.
Cover with the boiling water and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes and drain.
Mix next 6 ingredients and boil 10 minutes (vinegar, peppercorns, onion, parsley, bay leaf, celery salt).
Pour over mushrooms.
Cool.
Add 1/4 cup olive oil. Put in a tightly covered jar.
Shake well.
Refrigerate at least one day before serving.
Drain.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding
and
add
vanilla.
Stir
in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer
vanilla
wafers, bananas and cream mixture. May be topped
with
vanilla wafer crumbs.
You may also use a large Cool Whip and use half in the cream mixture and the other half to top with.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thickened and clear.
Cool at room temperature.
Add butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Mix in strawberries and pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with berries.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: vanilla yogurt ice cream
directions: Whip the whipping cream.
In large bowl, combine yogurt, sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container; cover. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: mocha nut butterballs
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until light.
Add next four.
Mix well; shape into balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: corn crunch cereal
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk.
Spread in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool until easily handled, then crumble through wire or whatever.
Toast dry in 350° oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except last two and place in casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and cover with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight; bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable layered salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix onions, celery and drained water chestnuts.
Layer on top of lettuce.
Mix peas and mayonnaise; spread on top of onion mixture. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Just before serving, add layer of bacon, followed by layer of sliced eggs and then a layer of chopped tomatoes.
Sprinkle entire dish with grated cheese.
If made shortly before serving, thaw peas first.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water in a large bowl.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in evaporated milk, sugar and salt until dissolved; stir into yeast mixture.

title: mama's banana cake and filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add rest of ingredients, except bananas. Mix well, then stir in bananas. Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Make a day ahead.
Refrigerate.
Boil and drain 1 pound spaghetti noodles.
Mix together Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
Toss 2 tomatoes, 2 cucumbers, 1 red onion and 2 bell peppers (diced) with mixture.

title: tacoed eggs
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs, cheese, onion, green pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir in a nonstick skillet until eggs begin to set.
Add taco meat; cook until eggs are completely set. Spoon onto warmed flour or corn tortillas and roll up; top with picante sauce.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O in bowl, 2 minutes, or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into Jell-O until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls/dough into rectangular cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and spread on dough.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually blend in lemon peel, milk and egg yolks.
Add lemon juice.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add all at once to butter mixture.
Mix until blended.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Blend into batter.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Divide among 12 greased or Pam sprayed medium-size muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.
(Can be put in loaf pans.)

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet.
Place 3 or 4 in bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/2 the soup, 1 layer of onions and peppers. Place remaining pork chops on top.
Repeat layer of onions, peppers and soup.
Pour 1/2 can water over top and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add beef and onion and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into large casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain. Add soups (undiluted), green chilies, enchilada sauce and milk. Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with 6 tortillas.
Top with half meat mixture and half the cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut in squares to serve.
Top each square with a dab of sour cream.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp pizza dip
directions: Drain shrimp.
Spread cream cheese on platter.
Layer cocktail sauce on cream cheese.
Add drained shrimp.
Top with olives, onions and mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese on top of pizza.
Chill at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: golfers stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a slow cooker.
Let cook slowly for several hours or until meat and vegetables are done. Needs no seasoning.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in container.
Add 2 tablespoons to each cup of boiling water or more; adjust to your taste.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Should be fairly wet.
If too wet, add dry bread crumbs.
Pack into small greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Place ingredients into a blender.
Mix together and pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans with beef
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef, adding portion of grated onion.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with ground beef and onion.
Stir until brown sugar is softened and no longer noticeable.
Pour in baking dish and place strips of bacon on top (optional).
Bake until bubbly and brown sugar skim begins to form on top.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and water; add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Smash shrimp with fork until fine. Add to cream cheese and mix well. Add horseradish and onion. Form into a ball and chill overnight. Cover with the cocktail sauce. Serve with crackers.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt over low heat, stirring often.
With toothpick, dip ball into chocolate mixture.
Remove toothpick when cooled.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and bay leaf with chicken stock in large pot.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Blend in flour and stir over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Gradually blend into stock mixture.
Add milk or cream, onion salt and salt.
Heat, but do not boil.
Garnish each serving with a dollop of whipping cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add oil and blend well. Add eggs and carrots and beat.
Bake in 3 layers or 1 tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes (55 minutes for tube pan).

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, sweet pickle and celery in a large bowl. Blend mustard with mayonnaise and stir into chicken mixture until well coated.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: gooey almond cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line an 8 or 9-inch round cake pan with aluminum foil.
Combine melted margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat in the eggs one at a time.
Add pinch of salt, almond extract and vanilla.
Stir in flour until ingredients are well blended.
Pour batter into the foil-lined pan.
Sprinkle the remaining sugar and almonds over top of batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until cake is golden brown.

title: my mother (mildred) icebox rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening and sugar; let come to boiling point. Don't let boil. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast cake in warm water. Add to first mixture when cool. Add self-rising flour (enough to make kind of stiff dough).
Beat and mix well. Set aside and let rise well (2 or 3 hours). Work down real good. Put in pan. Put in refrigerator overnight, then take out and make out rolls.
Let them rise real good and bake. When they start to brown, baste with butter. Continue to bake until done.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with marshmallows.

title: veggie chili con queso
directions: Drain beans and hominy.
Combine tomatoes, pintos, kidney beans, garbanzo beans, hominy, water, tomato paste, undrained chili peppers, cumin and garlic powder in a Dutch oven. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove from heat. Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: rich fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in large saucepan.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, add chocolate.
Beat well.
Add Marshmallow Creme and nuts (may omit nuts).
Remove from heat; stir well.
Pour onto 2 very large buttered platters or buttered cookie sheets.
Cool and cut into serving-size pieces.

title: red cabbage and cranberries
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, bacon, bacon grease and vegetables to liquid mixture and simmer 8 minutes.
Add 2 cups whole cranberries.
Simmer 15 minutes.
When serving, add enough cooked link sausages for 12 people.

title: aunt pat's vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled crust. Cut up cauliflower, broccoli, green onions, black olives and tomatoes (last).
Place on top.
Does not have to be baked.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
In second bowl mix peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Fold in whipped cream and put in pie shell.
Sprinkle with peanut chips.

title: russian carrot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in large heavy skillet.
Add onions and salt.
Cook over medium heat until soft, 5 to 8 minutes. Add carrots; stir.
Sprinkle in flour.
Cook and stir until carrots are tender, but not mushy.
If sticking to pan, add up to 3 tablespoons water.
Remove from heat.

title: sweet and sour ham balls
directions: Dissolve brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and water in pan.
Pour over ham balls and bake 30 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: half moon doughnuts and rolls
directions: Mix together in order as listed.
Let rise and roll in the cut pie shape, roll up, small end first, and bake or cut into doughnuts.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers. Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed of mixer 2 minutes. Blend in whipped topping.
Pour half mixture over graham crackers. Place second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour remaining pudding mixture over and cover with more crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours then frost.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Wash and drain strawberries well.
Cut them up.
Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and Jell-O together.
Add strawberries and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape as desired.
Cover with chopped walnuts.

title: lasagne
directions: Heat and brown the meat in skillet.
Crumble it and season with garlic.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes (drain well).
Season with 1/2 teaspoon pepper, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1 teaspoon oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: english toffee(candy)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, water and salt in a heavy saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, to 300°.
Watch carefully! Immediately pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool until hard.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Spread on toffee; sprinkle with nuts and press them down into chocolate.
Let set 2 to 3 hours; break into bite size pieces.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix and bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour. If using margarine, saute onion and celery in it.
May "bake" by microwaving 20 minutes on High.
I usually add 1/2 cup extra rice.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes in 325° oven.
Mix together Miracle Whip, Ranch mix and cream cheese.
Spread over cooled crescent rolls.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix pretzels, Cheerios and peanuts in large bowl.
Melt margarine.
Add seasonings, then mix thoroughly and brown in oven for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool and place in covered container.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup firmly packed brown sugar.
Cream well.
Blend in 1 egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, 1/2 teaspoon soda, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in one cup flour and one cup oats.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle one (6 ounce) package (1 cup)) semi-sweet morsels.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix and beat for 3 minutes the eggs, oil and sugar.
Add the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and pumpkin.
Beat 2 more minutes. Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
As soon as mixture forms, quickly pour onto a greased metal baking sheet.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt; mix well. Turn into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours or until custard is set.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Freeze.

title: glorious mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in a 2-quart saucepan and add water to cover.
Boil, uncovered, for 15 minutes until tender.
Drain them, adding milk.
Mix in oleo, sour cream and cream cheese until well blended.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with chives.
Serves 4.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Combine lemon Jell-O, boiling water and crushed pineapple. Cool for 45 minutes.
Add by folding in Cool Whip, Cheddar cheese and chopped pecans. Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Heat pineapple
juice and thicken with 1 tablespoon of cornstarch.
Cool slightly.
Mix bananas, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Save some nuts for topping.
Stir thickening gently over fruit.
Mix whip cream over fruit.
Top with nuts.

title: jamaica pepper pot
directions: Place meat and	bacon in large soup pot.
Add water and boil until meat	is
tender.
Then add spinach, sweet potatoes and spices.
Simmer
until sweet potatoes are cooked, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer for 15 minutes longer.
May be served with or without the soup meat.

title: crock-pot barbecue spareribs
directions: Place spareribs on rack in baking pan. Brown in a 400° oven for 15 minutes. Turn and brown on the other side for 10 or 15 minutes. Drain fat. Put ribs in crock-pot. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients (flour, butter and powdered sugar).
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Add sugar to eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over baked pastry.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt unsweetened chocolate with shortening.
Pour chocolate into mixing bowl.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares.

title: light ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly and pour into 1 gallon canister of ice
cream maker.
Pack ice and salt around canister. Process
according	to
manufacturer's
directions. Allow
ice cream to harden about 2 hours in freezer or repack canister
in ice and salt until serving time.
Makes 10 small servings.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a large Dutch oven over med.-high heat.
Add onion and next 4 ingredients; saute 5 min. or until tender.
Add flour, salt and red pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly until caramel colored (about 40 min.).
Add next 3 ingredients; cook, stirring constantly, 5 min. or until thick and bubbly.
Stir in crawfish; cook 5 min. or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with rice.
Garnish with chopped chives and ground red pepper, if desired.
2 lbs. frozen cooked crawfish tails, thawed and drained may be substituted for fresh crawfish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add other ingredients. Fill gallon jug to the top with water.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: roast tenderloin of beef(entree for dinner party)
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Place tenderloin in oven for an hour. Remove.
Allow to sit for 10 to 15 minutes; slice.
Perfecto. This is medium cooked.
If desire more rare, cook 45 minutes.
If desire well done, cook 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: spanish hamburgers(club member: john waters)
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain excess grease. When done, add chicken gumbo. Simmer 20 minutes. Place on hamburger bun.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine with first mixture, beat well and stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until done.

title: fruit cocktail dream cake(very easy)
directions: Mix together, beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Top with Hot Lemon Sauce or Lemon Glaze (recipes follow).

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Combine cheeses, basil and chives in a shallow bowl and mix well.
Cut breadsticks into strips and brush with olive oil.
Coat each breadstick in cheese mixture and twist.
Arrange on baking sheet and bake until lightly browned (12 to 14 minutes).

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk, salt, rice and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat, simmer for 1 hour, stirring frequently. Stir half of milk mixture into eggs and return to pan.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add drained pineapple.
Add cubed bread.
Mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once while baking.

title: vegetable spaghetti al forno
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to directions.
Saute vegetables in margarine just until crunchy, beginning with carrots and celery (they take longer), then add remaining vegetables.
In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan, layer half the spaghetti, dot with half the Ricotta and spread half the vegetable mix on top and half the Mozzarella. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Fill 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Service on croissants or pita bread.

title: white bread
directions: Scald 2 cups milk; remove from heat.
Add 2 eggs, two 1/4 teaspoons salt and 3 tablespoons sugar.
