Cool to lukewarm.
Soften 2 yeast cakes to the milk mixture; beat thoroughly.
Gradually stir in 3 cups flour to make dough that handles easily.
Turn onto floured board; knead until smooth, adding more flour if needed. Place dough in greased bowl; brush with 2 tablespoons melted shortening.
Cover; let rise in warm place 2 to 3 hours, until doubled.
Punch down, knead and shape into loaves.
Place loaves in well-greased pans.
Brush with melted shortening.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 45 minutes longer. Yields approximately 2 loaves.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Saute onion in butter. Mix first 7 ingredients.
Melt the butter for stuffing and mix. Spread on top of carrot mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all ingredients except beans. Cook on medium heat for 2 hours.
Add beans and continue to cook until desired thickness.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Add sugar and dry jello and dissolve in boiling water.
Add this to frozen strawberries and let stand until thickened to slush.
Break cake into small pieces.
Layer cake and jello, repeating until all is used up, ending with jello on top.
Ice with Cool Whip.
You can use small amount of Cool Whip between layers, also.
Use a 13 x 9-inch dish or pan.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter casserole.
Pour melted butter over the crushed crackers and mix well.
Layer in the baking dish 1 can cream-style corn, oysters and cracker crumbs, then 1 can corn, more oysters and crackers.
Mix oyster juice, Worcestershire sauce and the cream.
Pour over the casserole.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: meatball surprise
directions: Mix first 3 items together and add defrosted meatballs.
Heat and serve.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, milk, vanilla and 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May substitute pumpkin in place of sweet potatoes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix all except chicken and heat in microwave until warm.
In baking dish, add 1/2 of mixture in bottom of pan.
Place chicken in dish, cover with water (paprika on top) and bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove 3/4 of drippings; put in separate pan and heat over low heat.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Pour over chicken on plate or use as gravy.

title: divinity
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to hard ball stage. Slowly pour over the beaten stiff egg whites.
Beat in the vanilla and powdered sugar. Beat until gloss begins to leave.
Drop on wax paper.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oats and 1 cup milk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Heat griddle until water, sprinkled on it, dances across the surface.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter on griddle for each pancake.
When pancakes have a bubbly surface and slightly dry edges, turn only once to cook the other side.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Skin can be removed.
Wet each piece in water before you put in plastic bag.
Put ingredients in plastic bag.
Add chicken and coat twice.
Bake in pan at 350° for 40 minutes plus.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 300°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: charlie's cajun rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in a small amount of butter at very low heat until

they are transparent. Add this to the cooked rice. Stir in all other ingredients, except slivered almonds, and place in a buttered ovenproof dish. Garnish the top with plenty of the slivered almonds and sprinkle well with paprika.
Slip in the oven and bake at 300° for about 20 minutes. Great with any type of baked fish.

title: chicken & dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in pot of water with onion, carrots & celery till tender.
Remove chicken and cool.
Tear chicken from bones. Discard skin and bones.
Let chicken stock cool.
Remove fat from top of broth.
Reheat broth along with the chicken, carrots, onion and celery.
Add bouillon cubes and bring to boil.
Make dumplings by mixing baking mix and milk together.
Roll out and cut into squares - add to the boiling broth mixture.
Cook 20 minutes. Best served in soup bowls.

title: sensational double-layer pumpkin pie(lite)
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon evaporated milk with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: company carrots
directions: Cut carrots into strips, about 2 cupfuls.
Cook until they are tender and drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients together in a skillet and heat until well blended.
Add carrots and saute them about 10 minutes, stirring so that all the strips are coated with the sauce.

title: french toast
directions: Heat pan with butter.
Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl.
Dip bread in batter.
Sprinkle cinnamon on bread then put in pan and brown on both sides.

title: stacey's spicy chili
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck or deer.
Pour meat in a large stock pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 to 3 hours! Delicious as nachos or right out of the bowl.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Press together to form crust in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Beat thoroughly at high speed the confectioners sugar, 2 sticks margarine and eggs. Spread over crust.
Place sliced bananas over this.
Mix pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Spread over bananas.
Top with cherries.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Line pie plate with crescent rolls to make crust.
Brown hamburger with onions; drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Add green beans and simmer for two minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Do not peel squash.
Wash and slice thin.
Steam 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix squash, tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper, oregano and half of cheese.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top with remainder of cheese and thin bread crumbs.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add eggs to sugar and shortening mixture after creamed together.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Put 1/2 batter in bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Cover with fruit.
Cover with remaining batter.
Any kind of fruit may be used.
Serve warm with milk and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: zucchini meat pie
directions: Fry hamburg until brown with onion.
Line pie plate with bottom crust.
Add hamburg and onion.
Slice tomato and put on top of hamburg mixture.
Grate zucchini with skin over tomato.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Put in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off excess grease.
Chop canned tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Pour over pasta of your choice.

title: dressing
directions: Put hot water over bread and let stand a short while.
Saute onion and celery in oil.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff chicken or turkey or bake in pan.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crumble cookies and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat peanut butter, cream cheese, milk and 10x sugar until creamy and pour over crumbled cookies.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts on top.
Freeze overnight.
Keep in freezer.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Combine fruits and juice.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 x 5 x 9-inch bread pan.
Freeze overnight. Remove from freezer.
Break up.
Mix in mixer bowl.
Return to pan; cover.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 10.

title: night and day cookie
directions: Divide batter in half and put 1 cup cocoa in half of the batter.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: carolina layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green peas, onion, carrots and bacon bits in order listed, repeating layers, if desired.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar; spread on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over this.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Melt margarine in
hot potatoes.
Add other ingredients and pour in casserole baking dish.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: When grits are done, remove from heat and add butter and grated cheese and stir until melted.
Add the well beaten eggs. You may also add a few finely chopped green onions if desired. Pour into buttered or sprayed 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: hollandaz sauce for vegetables
directions: Place egg yolks, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce in blender. Melt butter, then slowly pour it into blender while blending other ingredients.
Serve over vegetables.

title: quickie tuna casserole
directions: Crumble chips retaining about 10 chips.
Cut up tuna and combine with chips.
Add about 1 can water to soup and pour over chips and tuna in casserole and top with whole chips.
Bake in moderate oven 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, margarine and sour cream well.
Add corns; mix well. Bake at 350° in a greased 8 to 9-inch square pan for 35 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
May be frozen and thawed to a slush. Add ginger ale before serving. Works well with other flavors of Kool-Aid.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water and chill until it starts to set. Add crushed pineapple and ice cream and beat well.
Blend in walnuts.
Chill until firm.

title: soy fried rice
directions: Heat oil, add eggs, mixing constantly
while breaking up with fork.
Mix eggs, onions, rice and soy sauce.
Blend very well and serve hot.
Note:
Can reheat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Get a pan.
Put on there and put it in oven.
Cook them.
Put plastic bags over them.
Cooks about 8 minutes.

title: pound cake recipe
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to butter and sugar.
Beat egg whites and add the 2/3 cup of sugar and beat.
Slowly add flour to butter mixture.
As mixture gets too thick to beat, add some of the egg whites and milk until all ingredients are used.
If margarine and Crisco are used, I add 1 tablespoon of butter flavoring.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked onions in their skins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line a small baking pan with aluminum foil and spray with vegetable cooking spray.
Trim off the root ends of the onions but leave the skin intact.
Place upright in the prepared pan and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until very tender. Remove the skins and discard.
Top each with melted butter or margarine.
Season with salt and pepper and serve piping hot, garnished with parsley sprigs.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in margarine.
Add shrimp (chopped); saute, then add the can of fried rice.
Heat and serve.

title: super creamy cocoa
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine cocoa and salt.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.
Over medium heat, slowly stir in water. Heat thoroughly, but do not boil! If desired, serve with marshmallows.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut steak across grain into diagonal strips about 3-inches long.
Combine butter and soy sauce.
Heat oil in a large skillet and brown the meat.
Add bouillon mixture and push meat to one side.
Add celery, mushrooms and onion; cook and stir for about 4 minutes.
Add the spinach and cook about 2 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: cream of mushroom chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done. Strip chicken in bowl.
Pour cream of mushroom soup into pan. Pour 1 cup of water in.
Stir out lumps. Pour chicken into the pan.
Mix together.
Warm for 10 minutes. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: annemarie zakian chewy squares
directions: Pour crumbs over melted margarine.
Layer other ingredients. Pour the can of milk over everything.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix on medium speed 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes.
Batter will be thin.

title: never fail cupcakes
directions: Put in bowl in order listed.
Do not stir until last item has been added, then mix thoroughly.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add onion, mix well.
Pour into crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for about 7 to 8 hours.

title: crab casserole with sherry
directions: Heat butter. Add flour and mix. Add cream and cook over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of the mixture into 1 to 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese. Add remaining crab mixture and top with rest of the cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.
Do not freeze.

title: zucchini and corn
directions: Simmer in butter (can use less) 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in greased casserole dish. Cook for 40 minutes at 300°.
Just before serving, cover with large marshmallows and return to oven (350°) until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water and add whipped cream cheese while still hot.
Pour juice from oranges over Knox gelatine until dissolved.
Then, add to first mixture.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Add mandarin orange slices.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: pina colada puffs
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with pineapple and amount of coconut to your liking (start with 1/4 cup).
Add the Cool Whip and mix well.
Using a sharp knife, cut anginettes in half "sandwich-style."
Spread the Cool Whip mixture on one half and replace the second half to make a sandwich.
Be generous; there is plenty of Cool Whip.
Chill several hours to soften cookies.

title: deep-fried fish and hush puppies
directions: Coat fish with cornmeal, reserving excess.
Fry fish in hot oil (370°), 2 to 3 minutes or until golden. Drain on paper towels; keep warm.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Blend bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Combine melted butter and garlic.
Roll each chicken breast half into a firm roll, skewer with a toothpick.
Dip chicken into butter mixture, then roll in bread crumb mixture. Arrange in a baking pan or glass casserole dish.
Pour lemon juice over chicken and drizzle with any remaining butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place in a 350° preheated oven and bake for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour, apples and cinnamon; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry tea slush
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over tea bags.
Cover and steep 5 min.
Remove tea bags.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Process chilled tea, frozen strawberries, and remaining ingredients in a blender until smooth and slushy.
Serve immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix salad ingredients together.
Add French dressing.
Add meat, beans and corn.
Toss.
Add corn chips just before serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs. Stir in milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and beat to a smooth batter.
Drop by tablespoon or pour from a pitcher onto hot, ungreased griddle.
Bake until underside is golden brown and bubbles appear over surface.
Turn and bake other side.
Makes about 20 (3-inch pancakes).

title: deviled ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spread on bread for sandwiches.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix yolks (I use a pastry blender).
Mix salad dressing and seasonings with yolks.
Fill egg white halves and garnish with paprika.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Mix pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade and orange Kool-Aid.
Add orange sherbet and enough cold water to make a gallon.

title: stromboli(clair family favorite)
directions: Thaw dough.
Cover with Handi Wrap so it doesn't dry out until you can roll it out.
Grease cookie sheet, rolling pin and dough. Roll dough on cookie sheet until it covers sheet.
Spread mushrooms, ham, cheese and pepperoni on 1/2 the dough (add as much as you like).
Fold dough over itself and pinch edges closed. Preheat oven to 150°.
Turn off and put stromboli in for 1 hour to rise.
Then, turn oven on to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Remove from oven and butter top.
Serve hot!
(You can also add other ingredients to inside!)

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground beef.
Add onion, garlic powder and tomato sauce. Cook 20 minutes.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Shred cheese.
Layer ground beef mixture, sour cream mixture, cheese and tortilla chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple strudel
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in buttered baking pan, 9 x 13-inches.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle over apples. Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Add flour and nuts.
Pour over thinly sliced apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southwestern chili bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Spread in pan. Bake for about 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, drain. Place in a large bowl. Add milk, salt and 1 Tbsp. butter. Beat until light and fluffy. Fold in egg, sour cream, cottage cheese and onions. Place in a greased 1 - 1/2 quart baking dish. Combine cracker crumbs and remaining butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: brunch oven omelet
directions: Grease an 8 by 8 baking dish with the 2 T. melted butter.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: frosted pineapple cake(no oil)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. In a large bowl, add eggs, sugar, vanilla, baking soda, salt and pineapple; mix well.
Add pecans to flour.
Add flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting over baked cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together except crackers and pour into greased baking dish.
Top with Ritz crackers (crushed) and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter and saute onions with Worcestershire sauce and butter.
Add meat and cook until done.
Add mushrooms, soup and sour cream.
Stir and simmer until hot through.
Boil noodles as directed on package and drain.
Gently stir the noodles into sauce.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add corn meal, salt, sugar and boiling water. Stir together well in medium large saucepan.
Cook until thick. Beat together eggs, milk and flour and stir into mixture in saucepan.
Stir well.
Melt 2 to 3 tablespoons butter in baking dish.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: ned mcwherter's banana pudding cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over 1 cup of oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray. Mix sausage, bread, cheese, eggs, milk, parsley, dry mustard and salt. Place in dish; cover and let set overnight in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable latkes
directions: Place vegetables in a strainer and press out liquid.
Transfer to a bowl.
Stir in flour and wheat germ.
In another bowl, mix together eggs, garlic and soy sauce; add to veggies.
(If mixture is watery, add additional flour or matzo meal.)
Heat enough oil to cover surface of a large, heavy skillet.
When hot, drop veggie mixture by soup spoonfuls into the pan.
Cook over medium heat until brown and crisp, about 10 minutes.
Turn and brown the other side.
Serve hot with additional soy sauce to taste.
Makes 8 pancakes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup with cream cheese; stir until dissolved, not boiled. Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and water.
Mix well the celery, onion and Miracle Whip, then add shrimp.
Put in mold to set for 2 to 4 hours.

title: easter eggs
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and marshmallow cream, stirring constantly until dissolved and starts to boil at side.
Take off stove and add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Cool slightly and butter hands.
Shape into eggs.
Cover with Hershey's chocolate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, chopped green pepper, celery, onion, pimiento and carrots.
In saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar and sauerkraut liquid.
Boil over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over vegetable mixture, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna; mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice, flour, eggs and sugar and cook until thickened; cool.
Add macaroni, pineapple, whipped cream and cooked mixture when cooled all together.
Add cherries for color (optional).

title: fruit snow
directions: In a 2-quart nonmetal container, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and freeze.
To serve as snow cones, scoop frozen mixture into 5 ounce drink cups or spoon into dessert dishes. Yields 14 (1/2 cup).

title: ground beef and tater tots
directions: Brown beef, onion and seasoning.
Pour into casserole dish and top with beans, then Tater Tots.
Mix milk and soup together and pour over top of all.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 box chopped dates.
Add 1teaspoon soda and let stand while above is mixed in usual manner. Add all together.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Combine olive oil, garlic, thyme and lemon juice.
Marinate pork chops in mixture for at least 1 hour.
Grill pork chops over medium coals for 25 to 30 minutes or until no pink remains.
Turn chops several times and baste during the last 5 minutes of cooking time with marinade.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: lettuce cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in bowl in order listed.
Refrigerate overnight or 5 to 6 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: rich cranberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to butter mixture.
Mix remaining flour (1/4 cup) with cranberries and nuts; fold into batter.
Batter will be very thick.
Spoon into a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until tests done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Tastes best when made the night before.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries, then add all other ingredients.
Chill.

title: beef and sour cream
directions: Roll pieces of round steak in flour and brown in vegetable oil in a hot skillet.
Place on plate to drain.
Save half of the fat in skillet.
Place thyme, onion, beef broth, mushrooms, salt and pepper in skillet with drippings from steak and mix thoroughly.
Add pieces of round steak to mixture in skillet and cook on low fire for 45 minutes.
When done, add sour cream and serve immediately over rice.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown onion and steak strips in shortening over medium heat until meat is cooked tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, beef bouillon and all seasonings to meat mixture.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add bell pepper strips and simmer an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
This is really good over white rice and tastes especially good reheated the next day.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour.
Spread 3/4 of batter into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with fruit filling.
Sprinkle walnuts over all. Drop remaining batter by tablespoons over fruit.
Spread batter over top (doesn't have to be spread over evenly on top).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage until tender (cut around core).
Brown bacon. Add and cook onion, minced garlic and green pepper.
Pour rice into mixture.
Add water.
Cook until water is gone.
Dump mixture into raw meat.
Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Roll in cabbage leaves which have hard vein removed.
Cook on low 45 minutes.
Add tomato soup mixed with vinegar and sugar.
Cook 1 hour more.

title: pie crusts
directions: Preheat the oven to 475°.
Mix the flour and salt in a bowl. Combine the syrup and milk and add all at once to flour mixture. Stir with fork until thoroughly mixed.
Shape the mixture into a ball and place it between two squares of wax paper lightly dusted with flour.
Roll the pastry into a circle large enough to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Spray pan with Baker's Joy.
Arrange pastry in pan.
Cut off the edges with a knife and press with a fork.
Prick the bottom all over with a fork.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before adding filling.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Cook ground sausage in pan. Add potatoes. Cook until brown. Drain fat. Warm tortillas according to desire. Scramble eggs. Divide ingredients evenly among the four tortillas. Season to taste with salsa or salt and pepper. Fold tortillas and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs slowly, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients alternately with the milk.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
(Test with toothpick to see if done.)

title: loaded with chips cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well. Combine oats, flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in morsels and pecans.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream sugar and butter.
Separate eggs.
Mix yellows with butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk a little at a time.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pan should be greased and floured.

title: impossible quiche lorraine
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese, onion and veggies evenly on bottom of pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender and process about 1 minute.
Pour in pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until browned lightly.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together.
Add a little water if necessary.
Deep fat fry until done.
Enough for 6 to 8 normal people.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms, vegetables and garlic in margarine 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Great topping for steak, chicken or burgers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potatoes.
Spray a casserole dish with Pam.
Layer potatoes, then soup mixture until pan is full.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli, carrots and cauliflowerets.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese; heat until melted.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, ice with:

title: veggie bean stew
directions: Place all ingredients in pot and cook for about 1 hour.

title: grandma's cherry spice cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the water.
Fold in cherries.
Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done.

title: chicken kalya
directions: Marinate chicken with salt, ginger/chili pastes, cumin powder, cardamom powder, cinnamon, cardamom and cloves.
Leave for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Spread over meat of choice to bake (or however you want to prepare it).
Remove bay leaf before eating.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender. Stir in spinach and next 5 ingredients.
Place artichokes in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon spinach mixture over artichokes and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: soup to nuts
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Remove and blend in cheese.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add to soup mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine into bottom of 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Pour 1 large can halved or sliced peaches or any fruit evenly into bottom of baking dish.
Do not stir!

title: zucchini dessert
directions: Mix crust until crumbly. Press half of mixture into 9x13 pan. Bake at 350° for 5-10 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread zucchini filling mixture (recipe to follow) over crust. Crumble other half over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco together.
Mix until it gets rich, so you can hold it together, then add cold water.
Put in pie plate and bake until done.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together egg and chicken broth.
Cut into dry ingredients.
Roll out and cut into small pieces; drop into boiling chicken broth and cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.

title: easy pierogi(potato cheese dumplings)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut all into same size and length, like 3/8-inch wide x 3/8-inch deep x 2-inches long.
Place in moderately hot oil or lard.
Use enough so spuds are not crowded.
When potatoes come to the surface, remove from fat immediately.
Reheat fat quickly on high heat.
The potatoes should now be plunged into the hot fat for the second time.
This must be done within 2 minutes from the first cooking.
Remove at once.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix together and spread in a cookie sheet.
Roast in oven at 250° for at least 2 hours, until lightly browned and crisp.

title: salmon soup
directions: In a medium bowl, mash 1 cup of the potatoes until smooth.
In a 4 quart pot, saute the onion, celery and carrot in the oil until tender.
Blend in the flour.
Add the tomatoes and using a spoon, break them up.
Stir in the milk, pepper, dill, cubed potatoes and mashed potatoes.
Simmer over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Gently stir in the salmon.
In a cup, mix the Monterey Jack and parsley.
Ladle the soup into 4 bowls.
Sprinkle each bowl of soup with 3/4 of the cheese mixture before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper in round slices and mix with cooled carrots.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more.
Drain to serve.
This will keep for two weeks in the refrigerator.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork and apple stew with dumplings
directions: Put milk and flour in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake until blended; set aside.
Heat oil in 4 - 5 qt. dutch oven over medium high heat.
Add pork and saute 2 minutes until no longer pink.
Remove with a slotted spoon to a plate.
Add onion, celery and carrots to pot.
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes until onion and celery have softened.
Add pork, rosemary, thyme and salt.
Cook 1 minute until fragrant.
Add broth, cover and bring to a boil.
Shake jar to remix milk mixture.
Stir into stew. Bring to a simmer and cook 3 minutes or until slightly thickened and creamy.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together in large bowl, pumpkin, brown sugar, white sugar, spices and salt.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Place in pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 50 minutes or until small cracks appear at the edge of the pie and center is firm to the touch. Makes 2 pies.

title: turkey meat balls
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Form into balls or loaf.
Fry balls in a sprayed frypan.
Brown a little; if any grease, drain. Add tomato sauce, Prego or Ragu and wine.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve with spaghetti or rice.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic and saut 5 minutes or until tender.
Add flour to sauce, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly 1 minute.
Gradually add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add shrimp.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in wine, whipping cream and parsley.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring often.
Can be served as a bisque or over angel hair pasta.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs until blended.
Beat 1 minute; stir in remaining ingredients except apples and nuts.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in apples and nuts; pour into pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: miss ima jackson chest pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal and flour.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Put in a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Put in bottom of baking dish.
Mix next five ingredients.
Put over bread.
Add bread for top.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over bread.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and spread 1 can mushroom soup over it.
Top with cheese and bake for 15 minutes without foil.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook diced potatoes and onions until tender (soupy) in just enough water to cover.
Add cubes of cream cheese to potatoes and onions.
Remove from heat.
Stir until cheese is melted.
To potato mixture, add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: bbq chicken
directions: Place whole chicken in crock pot.
Pour sauce over it and cook on low 8 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in paper cups and bake at 375°.
Fill 2/3 full in cupcake pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
(I double the recipe.)

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain off juice of cherries and reserve. Whip the cream cheese, adding cherry juice until all is blended in. Add thawed whipped topping. Fold in cherries and add crushed pineapple. Add marshmallows, nuts and coconut. Chill several hours in a 9 x 13 x 2 pan.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter on top of stove or in oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Lightly press down.
Sprinkle on top of crust in order:
the nuts, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and coconut.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until coconut is lightly browned.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: roasted cornish hens
directions: Combine margarine, chives and thyme.
Rinse hens.
Pat dry. Place hens, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Brush with some margarine and herb mixture.
Cover loosely with foil.
Roast in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Roast, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes more, brushing three times during roasting with the herb mixture.

title: skillet gravy
directions: In iron skillet, brown flour in hot meat drippings.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tan or light brown in color.
Add milk to desired consistency.
Cook until thickened.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, spices to taste and chilies.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Place tortillas in enchilada sauce, then layer 2 or 3 in bottom of greased oblong casserole dish.
Place layer of beef, 1/4 of soup and cheese on top of tortillas.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Put remaining enchilada sauce on top.
Pour on sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lee's chicken casserole
directions: Toss stuffing with 1 stick melted butter.
Put half mixture in bottom of long baking pan.
Mix chicken, mushrooms, soup, water chestnuts and sour cream together.
Put in baking pan.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot wassail tea
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; place over low heat.
Add sugar and spices; stir in boiling water and tea.
Heat, but DO NOT boil.
Yield: 20 to 25 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream potatoes and butter.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, sweet milk, baking powder, nutmeg, vanilla and flour.
Mix all together and add enough flour to roll out and cut.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Roll in sugar or spread with powdered sugar icing.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil, salt, debone and cut in pieces the chicken.
Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Combine the Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Break 12 soft tortillas in pieces.
Layer in an oblong casserole dish tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Repeat once more.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: luncheon dish
directions: Mix all but crumbs and almonds and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish (do not pack down).
Top with crumbs and almonds (almonds may be lightly browned first in 1 tablespoon butter if desired).
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
May substitute turkey, tuna, lobster or crabmeat for chicken.

title: fruit and cheese(usa)
directions: Peel and slice apples, cut cheese into 1/2-inch strips. Alternate cheese and apples around the outside of a round serving plate.
Place crackers in center of plate.

title: chicken-ham delight
directions: Put ham and cheese slices between folded whole chicken breasts. Toothpick together.
Salt, pepper and flour.
Fry in pan with as little grease as possible just to brown.
Add broth and sherry; cook 35 minutes over low heat.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill for 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball(club member: terah smith)
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 1/2 cup pecans. Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: bean dip
directions: Fry spices in hot oil until cumin turns brown.
Caution, it burns quickly.
Dump beans in on top and cook at medium heat until slow boil.
Mash beans, cook on low to desired consistency.
(My taste runs about 3 minutes.)

title: teriyaki tip steaks
directions: In shallow dish, place steaks.
In small bowl, combine sherry, soy sauce and garlic.
Pour over steaks.
In large skillet over medium high heat oil.
Drain steaks well, reserving marinade; pat dry with paper toweling.
Cook steaks in hot oil 1 to 2 minutes or until desired doneness, turning once.
Remove to warm serving platter.
Pour reserved marinade into pan.
Cook 2 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.
To serve, pour marinade over steaks; garnish with green onion.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with vegetables, rye bread or Hawaiian bread.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Mix together and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spoon topping over potato mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Can be put together and baked later (a day ahead).
Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry delight pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. When thick, add vanilla and red food coloring to make
a rich red.
Let mixture cool. Add strawberries. Place in pie shell and refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving. Decorate with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: brickle crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Lay out crackers on the cookie sheet, packing tightly.
In a medium sized saucepan, melt the butter, then add the sugar and boil, stirring frequently, for 2 or 3 minutes until sugar is completely dissolved.
Immediately spoon mixture over the crackers and bake for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle the chocolate and peanut butter morsels over the crackers, spreading evenly as they melt.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, then break into pieces.
Yield:
25 to 30 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dice up carrots, potatoes, onions and meat.
In a 6-quart pot, add carrots, potatoes and green beans to 2-quarts water and cook on high.
In a separate skillet, melt butter before adding meat pieces and onions.
Sprinkle garlic powder lightly on meat and onions while browning meat.
Once browned, add to vegetables.
Add tomato paste and assorted seasonings (to taste) along with 3 1/2-quarts water. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Let simmer on low setting for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kringla
directions: Combine sugar, egg, baking soda and flour.
Blend thoroughly into sugar mixture.
Divide dough thoroughly into sugar mixture. Divide dough in half.
Form each half into a long roll.
(If kitchen is warm, refrigerate 1 roll until ready to use.)
Cut off a narrow strip of dough.
Roll lightly with hands on lightly floured surface, into pencil-like strip, 7 to 8-inches long.
Form a figure 8 by pinching ends together tightly.
Bring pinched ends to center of the ring and tuck the pinched ends under.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients and set aside.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter beans
directions: Put beans in a covered saucepan with the ham hock and add enough water to come about 1-inch above.
Add salt; cover and simmer until beans are done, about 1 hour.
Check for salt. Serves 4.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Add soup, sauce, and chilies. Line baking dish with half of chips, add meat mixture. Cover with remaining chips. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Separate the whites and yolks of 3 eggs into 2 bowls.
Beat yolks until light. Add 3/4 cup milk, 1/2 cup melted butter and 3/4 cup sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
In another bowl, combine and sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add to egg yolk mixture and blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and carefully fold into the butter with a spatula.
Bake in a hot waffle iron and serve with desired toppings.

title: caramel dip
directions: Cream brown sugar and cream cheese together.
Add vanilla. Using any fruit, dip and enjoy.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown hamburg.
Combine soups, milk and sauce.
Mix layer of sauce, hamburg and chips.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange in large casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs (mixed) and then margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Trim with pimento strips.

title: chicken and vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken thighs and legs until done.
Take meat off bones and put in liquor along with remaining ingredients.
You may have to add
more
water.
Cook until vegetables are done. Good on cold days.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into 2 greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: maggie's salad
directions: Brown almonds in sugar until coated.
Cool and break apart. Mix together.

title: christmas eve bean soup
directions: Cover ham bone and beans with water; cook according to package directions.
When almost cooked, add potatoes, tomatoes, onion and salt and pepper.
Cook until beans are done.
Mash through soup with potato masher.
Add tomato juice and correct seasonings.
Add bacon drippings.
Stir and serve.
Serve with French bread and salad.
Delicious!!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries and water until berries pop; set off stove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and let set.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients together. Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir gently except for corn chips. Add chips when ready to serve.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash peas.
Cover with water.
Add ham bone and all seasonings.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until peas are tender. Add water if soup is too thick.
Should yield about 2 quarts soup. Serve piping hot and add croutons before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix oil, eggs and sugar well.
In separate bowl, sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples; mix well.
Spread mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread butterscotch chips on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. For best results, let stand 1 day.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cut roast into one-inch squares.
Put roast into a heavy pan. Combine tomatoes, vinegar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on very low heat (just a low simmer) for 5 to 6 hours until thick and tender.
Remove lid. Spoon out meat chunks and break apart with fork.
Return shredded meat to liquid and continue to cook uncovered to desired thickness and moisture.

title: mud pie
directions: Press cookie crumbs with butter into a 9-inch pie pan.
Put in freezer.
Mix ice cream, coffee and Kahlua.
Add whipped cream. Pour into pie shell; make level.
Put back into freezer for several hours.
Drizzle Hershey's chocolate syrup on top.
Serve.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and shape in ball.
Refrigerate overnight. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites and vanilla until frothy. Add sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on foil-lined cookie sheets.
Put in oven, turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for 8 hours.
May leave in oven overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger in oil and drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.

title: olive bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Slowly add milk and eggs.
Mix well, then add olives, pimentos and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Set aside for 20 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.
Great served with cream cheese.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat butter until light and fluffy, adding in sugars, a little at a time.
Beat in each remaining ingredient as listed, beating 1 minute with each addition, except for chips and nuts.
Stir these in with a mixing spoon.

title: daddy's quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Add first 5 ingredients together in kettle on stove. Bring to boil and cook for 1 minute. Turn off heat. Add peanut butter and oats to other ingredients. Mix well; drop onto waxed paper by tablespoon. Serve when cool. Makes approximately 30 to 36 cookies.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Cream together oleo and peanut butter.
Add vanilla, milk, sugar and salt.
Mix until creamy.
Frost cooled cake.

title: chicken with kraut
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken.
Add drained sauerkraut and potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix apple juice with rest of ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients. Coat fish with mixture. Bake or grill fish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or depending on thickness of fish.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add everything but cheese.
Cook until thick and bubbles on medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve in small bowls or cups and garnish with popcorn. Serves 8 to 10.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiffly.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Crush crackers.
Mix with egg whites and nuts.
Put in greased pie plate.
Bake 325° about 15 minutes.
When cool cover with cream and fresh coconut.
1/2 pt. to each pie.
6 to 8 servings.
Refrigerate.

title: build-a-better beef sandwich
directions: To assemble sandwich, spread cut surface of each half of croissant or roll with an equal amount of mayonnaise.
Arrange lettuce, cheese, tomato and beef over bottom half of roll; top with shredded carrot.
Close sandwich with croissant top.
Makes 1 serving.

title: fettuccine with creamy seafood sauce
directions: Coat a 2-quart saucepan with nonstick spray. Add the broth, scallions, basil, garlic and pepper. Bring to a boil.
In a medium bowl, whisk the milk and flour.
Stir the milk mixture into the broth mixture. Cook, stirring, over medium heat until the mixture thickens and begins to simmer. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.

title: tuna spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach and spread over bottom of greased pan.
Layer onion, then tuna and place sliced eggs on top.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over mixture.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add all other ingredients and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Check to see if done.
Ice when cool.

title: chocolate almond angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, adding the dry cocoa to the dry mix.
Add extract to the water for best mixing results.
Bake according to package directions.
Yield: 12 large servings.
And, for those of you wanting low fat content, this cake has only 140 calories and .3 g.
of fat!!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cakes in 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Let cool.
Slit into 4 layers (use string).
Add 2 cups boiling water to jello.
Add 10 ounces strawberries.
Add 3/4 cup cold water. Chill until syrupy. Make pudding (as directed).
Using round punch bowl, put 1 layer cake, jello, cake, pudding, strawberries, jello.
Chill overnight. Add Cool Whip as served.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Prepare gelatin using 1 cup hot water; cool.
Blend together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons warm gelatin.
Set aside.
Crush crackers and combine with 1 tablespoon sugar and butter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip milk until stiff.
Add gelatin to cream cheese mixture and fold into whipped milk.
Pour into crumb crust and refrigerate.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: arrias' ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add egg and molasses; mix again.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Take pieces the size of walnuts and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole(mexican)
directions: Mix enchilada sauce mix as directed.
Cook and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Grate cheese. Layer tortillas, cheese, chicken, olives and sauce.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven or until cheese is melted.

title: real homemade pizza
directions: Stir sugar into 1/2 cup warm water.
Sprinkle yeast over; let set 10 minutes.
Stir to blend.
Put flour and salt into bowl. Pour yeast mixture, oil and 1/3 cup warm water into bowl and mix together.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead lightly until dough is smooth.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; set overnight in the refrigerator.
Drain well and heat juice.
Add cornstarch to a little cold juice.
Add to rest of juice; cook until thick.
Cool, then add bananas, cherries and grapes.

title: strawberry poke shortcake
directions: Before the cake cools, using the tines of a fork or a bamboo stick, punch holes all over the top of the cake.
Mix the jello with 1/2 the required water; boil to ensure mixing.
Pour hot mixture over hot cake in pan; allow cake to cool.
Before serving, cake can be removed from pan or left in pan.
Pour sliced strawberries with some juice over the cake.
Cover entire cake with Cool Whip.
Serve.
Serves 12.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add alternately with milk.
Mash bananas and add.
Then add nuts.
Bake in a 10-inch stem pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or in 2 loaf pans for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: *Optional ingredients, or to your taste.

title: all butter pound cake
directions: Mix together into crumbs the sugar, flour, baking powder and butter.
Then add eggs and milk.
Mix on high speed for 10 minutes. Grease and flour tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: cheese sticks
directions: In a bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Add water and cheese and combine until a soft dough forms. (The dough should be soft enough to press through a cookie press or pipe onto a baking sheet.)

title: turkeyburger and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Brown ground turkey and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix (Bisquick) and eggs until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high, 1 minute with beater on high).
Pour into plate.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes, then add tomatoes and Mozzarella.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook seashells ala dente, drain.
Heat sauce, mix well with sauce.
Add pepperoni.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and 1/2 of the mozzarella, mix thoroughly.
place in buttered casserole dish, cover with remaining mozzarella and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Chill about 30 minutes and dip into the melted chocolate and paraffin.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: quick and easy chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Use whites for icing.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add egg yolks and other ingredients slowly.
Put in microwave and cook until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally. Put in baked pie shell (deep dish).
Ice with prepared egg whites.

title: dayton dip(delicious spicy taste.  may be frozen.)
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage over medium heat and drain.
Add milk, cheese, pimento and Tabasco sauce; simmer until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Place in a chafing dish or fondue pot to keep warm.
Serve with nachos, Doritos or Fritos.
Serves 20.

title: peanut butter
directions: You will need plastic knives and small paper plates.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese to this mixture. Mix with electric mixer well and then add pineapple (juice and all), 7-Up and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Refrigerate.
Put in large Pyrex dish.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
In separate bowl, mix egg, pineapple, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients to pineapple mixture, just until moist.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
Mix all well.
Pour in oblong baking dish and bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; spread in bottom of 13 x 17-inch casserole dish. Cut bread into cubes and spread over sausage.
Beat eggs and add about half as much milk as amount of eggs.
Pour mixture over sausage and bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top of casserole. Cook at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma's granola
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Melt margarine and honey and stir into dry ingredients.
Spread evenly on cookie tray.
Bake at 300°, stirring often, for twenty minutes.
When finished cooking, stir in raisins.
Cool before storing in airtight container. Yields 12 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar and salt. When moderately cool, add pineapple, cottage cheese and whipped cream.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Mix the Tater Tots and green onions.
Mix the soup, water and milk together.
Pour over Tater Tots and onions.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scarlatti scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut zucchini into 3 or 4-inch lengthwise sticks.
Place in a 10-inch baking dish.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle on onion and dot with butter or margarine. Combine cheese, sugar and seasonings.
Sprinkle over vegetables. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon magic pie
directions: Combine lemon juice, grated rind and milk.
Add two egg yolks and stir until blended.
Pour into crumb crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff enough to hold a peak.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Pile lightly on pie filling.
Bake until lightly brown, about 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bring water to boil; add oats.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs into mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats; beat well.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: crab soup
directions: In large pot, combine chicken broth, chicken stock, water and chopped celery.
Bring to boil and cook until celery is soft.
Add tomatoes (cut up) and juice and mixed vegetables.
Continue cooking until vegetables are soft.
Add Old Bay seasoning and crabmeat and simmer about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Blend soups and water into casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice over soup, then put chicken (salted) over this.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all, then cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish in microwave.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over the melted margarine. Do not stir.
Pour sliced fruit into mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until light brown.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: Combine butter and lemon juice.
In a medium bowl, combine bread crumbs, parsley and 1/4 cup of the lemon mixture.
Add paprika to remaining lemon mixture.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let dissolve.
Add water and stir.
Refrigerate and let congeal slightly.
Add cheese, nuts and whipped cream to jello mixture and mix lightly.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: 90 minute bread(4 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Mix in rest of ingredients except flour.
Add flour until dough is soft but not sticky.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: southern sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until blended.	Remove from heat and blend in evaporated milk gradually.	Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt, then beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in the chocolate mixture and pour
into	pie
shell.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over filling. Bake
at
for
minutes or until puffed and browned. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add shortening or margarine, salt, 1 tablespoon sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Pour out on floured board and knead a few times, then cut out and place in a pan.
Grease top and let rise in a warm place until double in size, about one-half to 2 hours.
Bake in moderately hot oven or until brown.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: candied bacon knots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line broiler pan with foil.
Position rack on top and coat with cooking spray.
Place brown sugar in a shallow dish. Tie each bacon slice into a loose knot.
Press one side of bacon in sugar to coat well.
Arrange in a single layer, sugared side up, on broiler rack.
Bake until crisp and bubbly. Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Transfer to paper towels to drain and cool. Can be held up to 3 hours at cool room temperature.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Add all ingredients in large pot. Add enough water to make it soupy. Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cover and simmer for about an hour.
The longer this simmers the better the flavor!

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Blend flour and margarine.
Add nuts.
Pat into 8 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients. Bake in two loaf pans 1 hour plus at 350°.
Test for doneness.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup apple juice in small bowl. Combine with remaining apple juice in saucepan and cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in apples, sprinkle with spices.
Put in pie shell and cover with top.
Bake in a 325° oven until done.

title: banana cake
directions: Add all together, them mix well.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: leah's all day stew
directions: Add all ingredients. Cook on low in crock-pot or oven 6 to 8 hours.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Stir in onions, celery and green pepper. Saute over medium heat until onions are clear. Add meat and cook until well browned. Season with salt and pepper. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup and sugar. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until celery and peppers are tender. Cook noodles in saltwater until tender. Drain. Mix noodles and meat sauce and place in greased large 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spicy garlic chicken pizza
directions: Combine chicken, 1/4 cup onion, garlic, vinegar, soy sauce, oil and peppers in a large bowl.
Stir to coat chicken.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Drain; reserving marinade.
Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large skillet; add drained chicken. Cook and stir about 3 minutes until no longer pink.
Stir cornstarch into reserved marinade.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Spoon evenly onto pizza shell. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
Top with 1/4 cup sliced green onions and almonds.
Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: cheesy tortilla corn
directions: Cook and stir onions and red pepper in 2 tablespoons of margarine in a large skillet until tender.
Reduce to low heat. Stir in corn and cheese.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Melt remaining ingredients in separate pan and stir in tortilla chips.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Spoon corn mixture into serving bowls.
Sprinkle with tortilla chips.

title: hawaiian chicken(serves 6)
directions: Spread spinach in baking dish.
Rinse chicken and pat dry. Arrange over spinach.
Combine soup, coconut milk, onion flakes, sugar and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over chicken; do not mix. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
May thicken with cornstarch, if desired.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Mix all of the above together and pour into an oblong cake pan.
Smooth out and cover.
Put in the freezer overnight.

title: stuffed artichokes with lemon garlic sauce
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, 2 cloves garlic (minced), grated cheese, parsley and olive oil.
Crumbs should be moist, not oily.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut tops and stems off artichokes.
Turn upside down and press firmly to loosen leaves.
Use your hands to stuff artichoke,
gently massaging the leaves to loosen.
Stuff generously!

title: peach cobbler (blueberry or blackberry)
directions: Mix 3 cups of peaches (or other fruit) with 3/4 cup of sugar.

title: orange cake
directions: Cook 2 hours at 300°.
Before removing from angel food pan. Glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar and 1 cup orange juice.
When cool remove from pan and store as fruit cake.

title: scandinavian vegetable salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
This will keep for up to 2 weeks.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Beat eggs in a bowl with a fork.
You do not have to use your mixer with this cake.
Add flour and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).
When cake is done, place marshmallows cut in half on top of cake while cake is hot.

title: easy barbecue(this is a simple summer recipe.)
directions: Brown ground round in a heavy skillet.
Drain fat. Add the barbecue sauce and simmer for at least 20 minutes or until mixture thickens a little.
Serve hot on small hamburger buns.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package and set aside. Boil potatoes until soft; drain and set aside.
Cook ground beef until done and add the tomato special and tomato paste.
Let simmer for a few minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix egg with milk.
Cut shortening in dry ingredients.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Knead lightly.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350°
until light brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, fruit cocktail and butter together.
Add flour and soda.
Pour in floured pan, then sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 20.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust!
Other flavors of Kool-Aid may be used for a variety of tastes.

title: 7-layer bars
directions: In 8 x 13-inch pan, melt butter; add vanilla.
Sprinkle on top in layers, the rest of the ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel pecan clusters
directions: Melt caramels; add cream and stir until smooth.
Add pecans to mixture and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm (will set quicker in fridge).
Pour a teaspoon of the melted cooled chocolate over each cluster and let stand until chocolate is firm.

title: round steak in gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces and flour.
Fry round steak in 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown the meat and then put into a casserole dish.
Add water to pan drippings (about 1 1/2 cups), then add 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Add sliced onion, salt and pepper. Pour soup mixture over meat in casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: In a bowl, alternate layers of cabbage and onion.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and let stand 3 hours.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until fork-tender.
Drain. Chill, peel and grate.
Turn into large bowl.
Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix gently until blended.
Turn into shallow buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add melted butter, milk and egg.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into muffin tins and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: three-step stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry beef in oil until it's not pink. Stir in soup, water and onion soup mix.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: no cholesterol popovers
directions: Grease 12 muffin pans.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Beat in milk and margarine.
Beat in flour and salt until blended.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 50 minutes.
Make slits in top of muffins and bake 5 more minutes.

title: irish potato pie
directions: With mixer, mash cooked potatoes.
Add eggs, sugar, milk and flavoring; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add margarine to top of pie.
Bake at 375° until firm.

title: quick fat-free pasta salad
directions: Cook the macaroni in boiling water until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix with the vegetables; add the dressing and toss to coat well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hotel twinkies
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients until smooth; gradually add dry ingredients.
Pour into miniature loaf pans and bake at 350° until spongy.
Cool and split in half lengthwise.
Add filling.

title: peaches in wine
directions: Divide peaches evenly among 4 dessert dishes.
Sprinkle each with 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Add splash of red wine.
Serve at room temperature.
Yields 4 servings.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Spread in bottom of 2-quart glass dish.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Saute onions and celery for 5 minutes.
Add ground beef; brown.
Add soup, rice, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole and bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake uncovered another 30 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin.
Cool and shred.
Combine cheese and margarine; heat until melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and seasoning.
Fold into potatoes and turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening until it crumbles to the size of a pea.
Beat eggs.
Add vinegar and cold water.
Add to shortening mixture and form into a ball.
This makes 3 large crusts.

title: light dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
If thicker consistency is desired, add more cottage cheese.
Chill. Serve plain or mix with chives, minced onion or other seasonings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix soup and water.
Stir in rice and seasoning packet.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour, until chicken is tender.
May add water if rice becomes dry before serving.

title: hot reuben spread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in small casserole dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve with cocktail rye bread or rye crackers.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done, then mash. Add butter, sour cream, cream cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Put mixture into large baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until filling is set and crust and mixture are golden brown.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in sprayed pan and cook until turns brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Heat the butter in large skillet over moderately high heat. Add the meat strips and onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until meat is browned and onion is fork-tender.
Remove from heat and add soup, sour cream and water.
Stir to blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and place over moderately low heat.
Cook 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
If desired, serve over cooked noodles.

title: hot crab bake
directions: In a large pan, melt butter and stir in flour. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in crab meat, chopped eggs, salt, pepper and parsley.
Spoon mixture in six 10-ounce casseroles or baking dishes.
Mix melted butter with bread crumbs. Sprinkle atop crab mixture. Top with slivered almonds. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: simple homemade pizza dough
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve the yeast and sugar in lukewarm water.
Let rise until foamy, about 15 minutes.
Mix the flour and salt in a large bowl.
Add the olive oil to the yeast mixture; stir to combine.
Add flour if dough is too sticky.
Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic, adding flour as needed. Takes about 5 minutes.
Pat the dough into a ball, then put in a large bowl.
Set in a warm place, covered with a clean towel.
Let dough rise about 1 hour.

title: four layer delight
directions: Melt your butter and mix with flour, butter and nuts. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: turkey club casserole(beryl)
directions: Mix turkey, soup and seasonings.
Mix cottage cheese and spinach in a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Alternate layer of noodles, turkey and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and repeat.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes until brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix all other ingredients; then add beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° approximately 35 minutes or until set.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl stir vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Stir in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; toss well.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and chocolate bits.
Pack firmly into ungreased 9 x 3-inch pan.
Top with melted margarine and chocolate bits.
Chill until set.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with bananas, blending well after each ingredient.
Stir in nuts.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Stir in cranberries, nuts and peel.
Combine egg, orange juice and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake in greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until done. Remove from pan and cool.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to directions. Crumble.
Make pudding according to directions.
Mix with Cool Whip. Crush candy bars. Layer 1/2 brownies, 1/2 pudding and 1/2 bars.
Repeat.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a large skillet melt butter, add rice and onion; cook until golden brown (watch so it does not burn).
Add bouillon, pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If needed add more water or bouillon, but make sure rice is done.
This is great with pork tenderloin patties, dipped in flour, browned and covered with sour cream and baked with rice.
Either one of these dishes can be baked or sit longer if meal is delayed.
Cover if over an hour.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix in nuts and M&M's.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet or baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter and arrange drained fruit over butter sugar coating.

In a bowl, beat the eggs until thick and lemon colored (5 minutes). Gradually add the sugar. Put in the fruit juice and flour. Add baking powder and salt. Mix the batter and pour over fruit. Bake until wooden pick thrust into center of cake comes out clean. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in a small saucepan.
Slowly add 1 cup boiling water and 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, reserved liquid, thawed strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with strawberry halves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in pan, then drain. Put ground beef, onion and salt into small casserole pan.
Pour green beans over meat mixture. Layer potato slices over green beans. Pour and spread tomato soup over casserole. Cover with boil and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Yields 6 servings.

title: favorite meat loaves
directions: Mix meats thoroughly with onion, celery and seasonings.
Soak cubed bread in milk; add eggs and beat with a fork or rotary beater.
Combine meat and egg mixtures.
Form into 2 loaves and roll in dry bread crumbs.
Place in shallow dish or baking pan. With the handle of a wooden spoon, make diagonal indentions in the top of each loaf, about 3 or 4 in each.
Spread the chili sauce in these grooves using about 1/2 cup on each loaf.
Pour boiling water around loaves.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato marmalade
directions: Sterilize 5 half-pint jars.
Peel tomatoes, chop coarsely and place in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add lemon and ginger.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.
Stir in sugar. Boil, uncovered and stirring often until thick, 25 to 30 minutes, or until candy thermometer registers 221°.
Ladle marmalade into hot jars.
